WEBVTT

1
00:00:39.790 --> 00:00:41.875
(WOLVES HOWLING)

2
00:00:43.126 --> 00:00:44.628
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

3
00:00:56.139 --> 00:00:58.267
JUNIOR: Nice night
to be born. huh?

4
00:00:59.685 --> 00:01:03.730
Apparently. my birth was not
considered a blessed event.

5
00:01:03.814 --> 00:01:07.401
That's me in the basket and
that's my mother carrying me.

6
00:01:07.484 --> 00:01:08.652
(JUNIOR CRYING)

7
00:01:12.489 --> 00:01:13.615
And that's my mother...

8
00:01:13.657 --> 00:01:14.658
(RINGING DOORBELL)

9
00:01:14.741 --> 00:01:15.951
...running away.

10
00:01:16.743 --> 00:01:18.662
Well. this can
still work out.

11
00:01:18.745 --> 00:01:19.997
Look at this place!

12
00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:21.331
(JUNIOR CRYING)

13
00:01:21.415 --> 00:01:22.499
Oh!

14
00:01:22.916 --> 00:01:24.168
Madam!

15
00:01:29.506 --> 00:01:31.466
Aw!

16
00:01:33.886 --> 00:01:35.429
Oh.

17
00:01:36.889 --> 00:01:41.810
Who on earth would want
to abandon such a wonderful little baby boy?

18
00:01:41.977 --> 00:01:42.978
(GASPS)

19
00:01:45.272 --> 00:01:47.316
(GROWLING)

20
00:01:49.526 --> 00:01:50.986
(BARKING)

21
00:02:00.746 --> 00:02:01.747
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

22
00:02:03.207 --> 00:02:05.125
But I am not dreaming.

23
00:02:05.209 --> 00:02:07.544
There's one thing I know
I really know.

24
00:02:07.628 --> 00:02:11.423
and that is that there's no such thing in the
world as a bad boy. I'm sure of that.

25
00:02:11.507 --> 00:02:13.842
JUNIOR: Oh. what does he know?

26
00:02:25.812 --> 00:02:27.898
What a strange-looking dog!

27
00:02:28.398 --> 00:02:29.691
(HISSING)

28
00:02:31.735 --> 00:02:33.570
I'll bet he's hungry.

29
00:02:37.074 --> 00:02:38.492
This looks good.

30
00:02:46.625 --> 00:02:47.918
(BELCHING)

31
00:02:50.546 --> 00:02:53.465
Diver Dan. Diver Dan.
surface. surface!

32
00:03:07.729 --> 00:03:09.273
These are my favorite toys.

33
00:03:09.356 --> 00:03:11.275
Who am I kidding?
They're my only toys.

34
00:03:12.568 --> 00:03:14.361
That's my dad.

35
00:03:17.114 --> 00:03:18.949
Oh. so you want to
play rough. huh?

36
00:03:26.456 --> 00:03:28.125
I was just kidding!

37
00:03:28.166 --> 00:03:31.128
Oh. no! Not the nuns.
not the nuns!

38
00:03:38.844 --> 00:03:41.471
Gee. I wonder
if penguins can fly.

39
00:03:44.516 --> 00:03:46.518
Help!

40
00:03:47.728 --> 00:03:50.606
Oh. no!

41
00:03:50.772 --> 00:03:51.982
Help!

42
00:03:52.065 --> 00:03:55.360
JUNIOR: You see? No one
really ever accepted me.

43
00:03:55.444 --> 00:03:57.237
Who'd be that caring?

44
00:03:57.321 --> 00:03:59.072
Who'd be that loving?

45
00:03:59.156 --> 00:04:00.824
Who'd be that dumb?

46
00:04:00.866 --> 00:04:05.162
Oh. listen to this.
It says here that Henry is a strong name.

47
00:04:05.245 --> 00:04:07.331
"He's loyal and loving."

48
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:09.333
Henry?

49
00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:10.459
Hank.

50
00:04:10.501 --> 00:04:12.669
Henri.
That sounds like a loser.

51
00:04:12.753 --> 00:04:15.172
No. come on.
think about it. Henry. Hank.

52
00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:17.132
Hank Aaron.
that's a winner.

53
00:04:17.173 --> 00:04:19.176
"How was school today. Hank?"
"Great. Dad!"

54
00:04:19.259 --> 00:04:21.303
"Okay. Hank."
That's got potential.

55
00:04:21.345 --> 00:04:22.679
Let's put a star
down next to Henry.

56
00:04:22.721 --> 00:04:24.389
No. I don't like it.

57
00:04:24.473 --> 00:04:26.350
Oh. what about Donald?

58
00:04:26.391 --> 00:04:28.936
It says here that
Donald is wealthy and powerful.

59
00:04:29.019 --> 00:04:31.104
Now that's the kind
of kid I want.

60
00:04:31.188 --> 00:04:34.024
Oh. okay. Look. Flo.
I'll be happy no matter how he turns out.

61
00:04:34.066 --> 00:04:35.734
After all.
he'll be our child.

62
00:04:35.817 --> 00:04:37.945
But it wouldn't hurt if he's
also chairman of the board.

63
00:04:38.028 --> 00:04:39.696
So. when is
your child due?

64
00:04:40.489 --> 00:04:44.910
Oh. well. I'm not really pregnant
yet. We're just planning ahead.

65
00:04:44.993 --> 00:04:47.162
Yeah. a little wishful
thinking never hurt anyone.

66
00:04:48.038 --> 00:04:52.960
You know. here at the clinic.
we pride ourselves on a 99% success rate.

67
00:04:53.043 --> 00:04:54.920
-Little Henry Healy.
-Donald.

68
00:04:55.003 --> 00:04:57.881
Unfortunately.
there is that other 1%.

69
00:04:57.923 --> 00:04:59.424
And you're it.

70
00:04:59.508 --> 00:05:01.802
I'm sorry. but the test
came back positive.

71
00:05:01.885 --> 00:05:03.929
Oh. positive.
I mean. that's good.

72
00:05:04.012 --> 00:05:05.389
No. positive is bad.

73
00:05:05.430 --> 00:05:07.808
No. positive is good.
negative is bad.

74
00:05:07.891 --> 00:05:09.560
No. negative is good.

75
00:05:09.601 --> 00:05:12.104
You see. you are
positively infertile.

76
00:05:12.187 --> 00:05:15.691
You mean. we've been doing
it every night for nothing?

77
00:05:17.401 --> 00:05:20.737
Let me explain.
This is your uterus.

78
00:05:22.906 --> 00:05:25.450
Well. that purple thing
is your cervix.

79
00:05:25.534 --> 00:05:28.453
These green things here
are your fallopian tubes and this...

80
00:05:29.580 --> 00:05:32.541
That's not supposed to happen.
Toss me that. Thanks.

81
00:05:32.583 --> 00:05:34.418
This yellow thing
is your ovary.

82
00:05:35.294 --> 00:05:37.671
Fits right in
there. like that.

83
00:05:37.754 --> 00:05:40.424
Well. you know what?
It doesn't matter.

84
00:05:40.465 --> 00:05:44.052
Because you don't even have
a yellow thing and your green thing is brown.

85
00:05:45.095 --> 00:05:48.515
(STAMMERING) Doctor.
are you absolutely sure there's no hope?

86
00:05:48.599 --> 00:05:49.850
None whatsoever.

87
00:05:50.601 --> 00:05:54.104
Oh. but there are alternatives
to having your own child.

88
00:05:56.315 --> 00:05:58.567
JUNIOR: I tried to like
it at the orphanage.

89
00:05:58.609 --> 00:06:01.778
but then I became
interested in photography.

90
00:06:05.407 --> 00:06:08.160
After that. things
kind of went downhill.

91
00:06:15.626 --> 00:06:19.046
Eat all of your stew.
children.

92
00:06:19.129 --> 00:06:22.466
A growing body
needs nutrition.

93
00:06:22.508 --> 00:06:23.926
And discipline.

94
00:06:23.967 --> 00:06:27.971
Well. if it's so nutritious.
how come I don't see you eating it?

95
00:06:28.055 --> 00:06:30.224
GIRL: Junior! Junior!

96
00:06:37.856 --> 00:06:42.069
JUNIOR: I was never really sure
which one I got. nutrition or discipline.

97
00:06:52.871 --> 00:06:54.623
What do they put
in this stuff?

98
00:06:54.665 --> 00:06:56.250
Hey. Junior. come on.
just eat your lunch.

99
00:06:56.333 --> 00:06:58.168
Please don't get us
in trouble again.

100
00:07:02.673 --> 00:07:03.841
(CHILDREN CHUCKLING)

101
00:07:04.967 --> 00:07:06.510
Who are they kidding?

102
00:07:06.552 --> 00:07:07.803
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

103
00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:17.855
Junior!

104
00:07:18.689 --> 00:07:21.149
And what happened
to your lunch?

105
00:07:21.191 --> 00:07:24.194
It was so delicious.
I just gobbled it all up!

106
00:07:31.535 --> 00:07:33.245
I can't believe it.

107
00:07:33.328 --> 00:07:37.207
For once. you behaved yourself.
Thank you. Lord!

108
00:07:38.625 --> 00:07:40.043
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

109
00:07:44.965 --> 00:07:46.008
Ow!

110
00:07:46.049 --> 00:07:48.218
Hey. lady.
hands off the merchandise!

111
00:07:48.302 --> 00:07:50.304
I gotta hear
out of that thing!

112
00:07:50.554 --> 00:07:51.889
(SCREAMING)

113
00:07:55.767 --> 00:07:59.354
All right. mister. you know the routine.
Start mopping.

114
00:07:59.396 --> 00:08:01.440
Sister. I'm all
packed to go.

115
00:08:01.523 --> 00:08:04.693
There's my
favorite little boy.

116
00:08:04.735 --> 00:08:07.321
I'm going to miss
you so much.

117
00:08:07.404 --> 00:08:09.698
Miss him?
Where's he going?

118
00:08:09.740 --> 00:08:11.992
Haven't you heard?
I'm getting adopted.

119
00:08:12.075 --> 00:08:15.412
I got a new mommy and daddy
and they're so nice.

120
00:08:15.454 --> 00:08:16.705
Really?

121
00:08:16.747 --> 00:08:18.081
Yes.

122
00:08:18.123 --> 00:08:21.001
Good little boys
get good homes.

123
00:08:22.085 --> 00:08:25.380
Bad little boys
get something else!

124
00:08:27.424 --> 00:08:32.179
JUNIOR: Big deal. If you have to be a creep
like Freddy. I don't want a family.

125
00:08:38.727 --> 00:08:40.604
MAN ON TV: A man described
as "evil incarnate."

126
00:08:40.687 --> 00:08:42.898
A man called
"the fiend of the century."

127
00:08:42.940 --> 00:08:45.317
Where are my cartoons?

128
00:08:45.400 --> 00:08:47.402
They did me wrong!
They had it coming!

129
00:08:47.444 --> 00:08:48.737
REPORTER: All 34 of them?

130
00:08:48.779 --> 00:08:50.155
You bet they did!

131
00:08:50.239 --> 00:08:53.742
Geez. this guy's pretty popular.
He's on every channel.

132
00:08:54.660 --> 00:08:56.161
Since he escaped a week ago.

133
00:08:56.245 --> 00:08:59.998
residents of the neighboring three states
have been afraid to leave their home.

134
00:09:00.082 --> 00:09:02.459
Beck. known infamously
as the Bow Tie Killer.

135
00:09:02.501 --> 00:09:06.004
was finally recaptured this afternoon and
is now on his way back to federal prison.

136
00:09:06.088 --> 00:09:08.006
Why is everybody
always picking on me?

137
00:09:08.090 --> 00:09:11.176
I'm not a bad guy!
I'm just misunderstood!

138
00:09:11.260 --> 00:09:13.679
Nobody cares about me but me!

139
00:09:13.762 --> 00:09:15.138
JUNIOR: What a
good-looking guy.

140
00:09:15.222 --> 00:09:18.350
MAN ON TV: Authorities have confirmed that
because of this attempted prison break.

141
00:09:18.433 --> 00:09:21.895
Beck would have to serve additional time
to an already lengthy sentence.

142
00:09:21.979 --> 00:09:26.316
When he is returned to the federal prison.
Beck will be placed under...

143
00:09:35.742 --> 00:09:36.785
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

144
00:09:36.827 --> 00:09:38.328
WOMAN: There he is!

145
00:09:40.664 --> 00:09:42.165
MAN: Here. son.

146
00:09:44.001 --> 00:09:46.879
WOMAN: Do you see him?
There's our boy!

147
00:09:49.339 --> 00:09:50.382
Oh. honey!

148
00:09:50.465 --> 00:09:53.510
MAN: Your room's all ready.
Packed it full of toys.

149
00:09:53.594 --> 00:09:55.846
WOMAN: Oh. gosh.
I'm so excited!

150
00:10:09.693 --> 00:10:11.195
Have a good day. honey.

151
00:10:12.154 --> 00:10:14.865
Look. why don't you just
take a look at this adoption literature?

152
00:10:14.907 --> 00:10:16.533
We can talk
about it tonight.

153
00:10:16.617 --> 00:10:18.202
Why don't you look
at it yourself?

154
00:10:18.243 --> 00:10:21.580
I don't wear second-hand clothes
and I won't have a second-hand kid.

155
00:10:21.663 --> 00:10:22.873
Adoption is out!

156
00:10:22.915 --> 00:10:24.458
Okay. all right.

157
00:10:26.668 --> 00:10:27.711
Fine.

158
00:10:28.253 --> 00:10:30.255
BIG BEN: (OVER PA)
Welcome to Big Ben's.

159
00:10:30.339 --> 00:10:33.217
the sporting goods store
that has everything.

160
00:10:33.258 --> 00:10:37.596
Sporting goods made by
Americans for Americans.

161
00:10:37.679 --> 00:10:41.517
And my fellow Americans.
don't forget to vote for Big Ben for mayor!

162
00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:43.519
Hey. mister.
do you work here?

163
00:10:43.560 --> 00:10:45.562
I sure do. son.
How can I help you?

164
00:10:45.604 --> 00:10:48.607
Well. I'm looking
for a canteen with a compass on it.

165
00:10:48.690 --> 00:10:51.235
I saw your commercial
and they said you have everything.

166
00:10:51.276 --> 00:10:52.819
You bet we do.
This is Big Ben's.

167
00:10:52.903 --> 00:10:56.114
We got canteens
365 days a year.

168
00:10:56.198 --> 00:10:57.908
Now. which one of these
can I fix you up with?

169
00:10:57.991 --> 00:10:59.326
I like this blue one.

170
00:10:59.409 --> 00:11:01.578
Hey. sport. where
did you run off to?

171
00:11:01.662 --> 00:11:04.248
Oh. this man was
helping me find my canteen.

172
00:11:04.331 --> 00:11:06.792
Oh. hey. I'm sorry.
I hope Hank wasn't bothering you.

173
00:11:06.875 --> 00:11:10.128
I guess he's kinda excited
about this camping trip we're going on.

174
00:11:10.212 --> 00:11:11.880
You two really must have
a lot of fun together.

175
00:11:11.922 --> 00:11:15.384
Yeah. these little rascals
really make life worth living.

176
00:11:15.425 --> 00:11:17.970
I mean. what the heck
else are we here for. eh. partner?

177
00:11:18.053 --> 00:11:19.680
-Yeah.
-Come on. buddy. let's go!

178
00:11:21.223 --> 00:11:22.641
-Did you get what you wanted?
-Yeah.

179
00:11:22.724 --> 00:11:24.977
-Okay. thanks a lot. buddy.
-My pleasure.

180
00:11:26.270 --> 00:11:27.604
BIG BEN: (OVER PA) Little Ben!

181
00:11:27.688 --> 00:11:28.897
What?

182
00:11:28.939 --> 00:11:32.526
Get your little butt in here.
I got a big surprise for you.

183
00:11:33.861 --> 00:11:37.281
That's right. Big Ben's
is 100% American.

184
00:11:38.740 --> 00:11:40.534
I'm selling the
store to the Japs.

185
00:11:41.785 --> 00:11:42.995
(STAMMERING) But...

186
00:11:43.078 --> 00:11:44.830
(MOCKING) But...
What?

187
00:11:44.913 --> 00:11:46.707
Thought I was gonna
leave it to you one day?

188
00:11:46.790 --> 00:11:48.041
Uh. yes.

189
00:11:48.125 --> 00:11:49.710
Well. I'm not.

190
00:11:49.793 --> 00:11:51.837
I'm selling to the
Hirohito Corporation.

191
00:11:53.297 --> 00:11:55.799
Well. I still get the land.
right. Dad?

192
00:11:55.883 --> 00:11:58.302
No. you won't.
No. no.

193
00:11:58.343 --> 00:12:01.597
I'm selling that. too.
Everything from here to the river.

194
00:12:01.638 --> 00:12:03.098
What?

195
00:12:03.140 --> 00:12:05.184
Dad! I can't
believe this.

196
00:12:05.267 --> 00:12:09.813
I slaved for you for over 10 years
without even a raise or a promotion.

197
00:12:10.814 --> 00:12:13.025
Is there a lesson to be
learned from all of this?

198
00:12:13.108 --> 00:12:14.151
A lesson?

199
00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:15.694
How about.
don't trust anyone?

200
00:12:15.777 --> 00:12:17.029
Not even your
own father?

201
00:12:17.112 --> 00:12:19.323
Especially
your own father.

202
00:12:19.406 --> 00:12:21.450
You know your problem?
You're too nice.

203
00:12:21.491 --> 00:12:24.411
I expected a little
back-stabbing from you.

204
00:12:24.494 --> 00:12:27.414
Some ruthless scrambling
to get to the top.

205
00:12:27.497 --> 00:12:30.292
But you stubbornly refuse
to follow my example.

206
00:12:36.381 --> 00:12:39.843
JUNIOR: Today's my birthday.
Look what they gave me.

207
00:12:39.927 --> 00:12:41.595
NUN: Junior!

208
00:12:41.678 --> 00:12:43.222
Junior!

209
00:12:43.305 --> 00:12:45.641
What is taking
you so long?

210
00:12:45.682 --> 00:12:48.185
We start serving
dinner in 20 minutes.

211
00:12:48.227 --> 00:12:49.978
I only got two hands.

212
00:12:50.020 --> 00:12:55.025
And I want these
pots so shiny. I can see my face in them!

213
00:12:55.108 --> 00:12:57.194
This one kinda
looks like you.

214
00:12:57.236 --> 00:13:00.239
All right. smart mouth.
now you're gonna pay for it.

215
00:13:05.536 --> 00:13:06.870
Junior!

216
00:13:06.954 --> 00:13:08.956
Yikes! A penguin
in a pot!

217
00:13:09.206 --> 00:13:11.500
Help!

218
00:13:16.880 --> 00:13:19.383
JUNIOR: I wonder if they
want me to do the floor!

219
00:13:20.300 --> 00:13:21.301
(GASPS)

220
00:13:21.885 --> 00:13:23.470
(SCREAMING)

221
00:13:30.102 --> 00:13:32.104
Junior!

222
00:13:34.523 --> 00:13:36.483
(CROWD CHEERING)

223
00:13:36.567 --> 00:13:38.235
BEN: Okay. kids.
huddle up. all right.

224
00:13:38.318 --> 00:13:40.153
Now. listen.
we got three more innings.

225
00:13:40.237 --> 00:13:43.365
Remember. if we win.
we all get ice cream.

226
00:13:43.407 --> 00:13:44.950
ALL: Yay!

227
00:13:45.033 --> 00:13:46.910
And if we lose...

228
00:13:46.952 --> 00:13:49.204
What the hay?
We'll have ice cream anyway. all right?

229
00:13:49.246 --> 00:13:50.831
Go take the field.
I'm proud of you!

230
00:13:50.914 --> 00:13:53.333
Look mean out there!
Look tough!

231
00:13:53.417 --> 00:13:56.753
Little Ben. can I talk
to you for a second?

232
00:13:56.837 --> 00:13:59.798
I told you. Roy. I don't care how many runs
you score. we're not gonna forfeit.

233
00:13:59.882 --> 00:14:02.843
No! Hey. I don't
care about this game.

234
00:14:02.926 --> 00:14:04.636
We got this thing
won already.

235
00:14:04.720 --> 00:14:07.806
I just came over to share
my happiness with you. Little Ben.

236
00:14:07.890 --> 00:14:10.058
Harriet had a sonogram.
Take a look.

237
00:14:11.018 --> 00:14:12.019
What is that?

238
00:14:12.102 --> 00:14:13.228
It's a boy!

239
00:14:13.270 --> 00:14:15.022
Hey. congratulations.
Roy.

240
00:14:15.105 --> 00:14:16.815
And I got one
of these for you.

241
00:14:16.899 --> 00:14:18.483
-Open up.
-I don't smoke.

242
00:14:18.567 --> 00:14:21.028
Come on. open up.
Open up!

243
00:14:24.740 --> 00:14:28.327
ANNOUNCER: It's a home run
for the Chieftains!

244
00:14:28.410 --> 00:14:31.622
Well. what do you know?
Another home run.

245
00:14:31.705 --> 00:14:33.165
Way to go. Gary!

246
00:14:34.958 --> 00:14:36.543
(NUNS CLAMORING)

247
00:14:39.713 --> 00:14:41.632
PEABODY: Can you
please pipe down?

248
00:14:41.673 --> 00:14:43.342
Quiet down.
quiet down!

249
00:14:43.425 --> 00:14:44.718
(ALL CLAMORING)

250
00:14:44.801 --> 00:14:46.845
Ladies. please.
Can you please quiet down?

251
00:14:49.890 --> 00:14:51.642
Sisters. can you quiet down?

252
00:14:51.683 --> 00:14:53.477
Can you act like nuns?

253
00:14:54.728 --> 00:14:55.854
Okay.

254
00:14:55.938 --> 00:14:58.982
Now. there's
absolutely no proof

255
00:14:59.024 --> 00:15:02.486
that Junior was in any way
connected with today's tragedy.

256
00:15:02.569 --> 00:15:04.196
Who needs proof?
He's evil.

257
00:15:04.279 --> 00:15:06.657
He has a wicked mind.
Look what he did in art class. Skeletons.

258
00:15:06.698 --> 00:15:07.783
Headless corpses.

259
00:15:07.824 --> 00:15:09.368
Monsters devouring
human flesh.

260
00:15:09.451 --> 00:15:10.994
All right. look. look.

261
00:15:11.078 --> 00:15:15.958
I don't claim to be some kind
of brilliant psychologist. I'm not.

262
00:15:15.999 --> 00:15:20.671
All I'm saying is maybe
all the child needs is to be loved.

263
00:15:20.712 --> 00:15:23.298
Oh. let's cut the crap.
Mr. Peabody.

264
00:15:23.340 --> 00:15:26.760
Either Junior goes or you
find yourself some new nuns.

265
00:15:26.844 --> 00:15:29.429
No. no. no. please. please.
don't hyperventilate.

266
00:15:29.513 --> 00:15:32.683
Don't...
Just take a deep breath and relax.

267
00:15:32.766 --> 00:15:37.813
The only way we can straighten this out is by
hearing what Junior has to say about it.

268
00:15:48.031 --> 00:15:49.908
I'm sorry. sisters.

269
00:15:49.992 --> 00:15:53.912
Please. please don't make
me lift those heavy stones

270
00:15:53.996 --> 00:15:57.082
and please don't make me
scrub those dirty toilets.

271
00:15:57.165 --> 00:15:58.876
I just want to
be a good boy.

272
00:15:58.917 --> 00:16:00.294
I promise.

273
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:03.714
You see that?
He said he's sorry.

274
00:16:03.755 --> 00:16:05.883
Please. give me
another chance.

275
00:16:05.966 --> 00:16:09.428
I just want to learn my
lessons and do my studies

276
00:16:09.511 --> 00:16:11.930
so I can be smart
and become a priest.

277
00:16:12.014 --> 00:16:14.892
There. You see that?
A priest.

278
00:16:14.975 --> 00:16:17.561
A priest. It's like
a nun with a jacket.

279
00:16:17.603 --> 00:16:21.064
It's a boy nun.
He wants to be a boy nun.

280
00:16:21.106 --> 00:16:26.153
Let me tell you something.
It takes a big man to admit his mistakes.

281
00:16:26.236 --> 00:16:28.655
And there is a big man.

282
00:16:28.739 --> 00:16:33.493
It is in the opinion of myself
and my agency of which I represent.

283
00:16:33.577 --> 00:16:37.581
that Junior will not be
removed from this orphanage.

284
00:16:37.664 --> 00:16:40.250
Removed? What do
you mean "removed"?

285
00:16:40.292 --> 00:16:41.835
Don't worry about it.
Junior.

286
00:16:41.919 --> 00:16:44.338
You see. the nuns just
made a suggestion

287
00:16:44.421 --> 00:16:47.424
you might be happier
outside of the orphanage.

288
00:16:47.466 --> 00:16:50.260
(LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY)

289
00:16:50.302 --> 00:16:51.428
What's so funny?

290
00:16:51.470 --> 00:16:53.222
You are.
you stupid dick.

291
00:16:54.431 --> 00:16:55.849
You see? He's wicked!

292
00:16:55.933 --> 00:17:00.103
You're not saying you'd rather not
be in the orphanage. are you?

293
00:17:00.145 --> 00:17:01.146
(EXCLAIMING)

294
00:17:01.230 --> 00:17:03.774
Think much. pea brain?
I want out!

295
00:17:04.066 --> 00:17:07.319
You see. Mr. Peabody?
The child is incorrigible.

296
00:17:07.402 --> 00:17:10.364
I'm what? Why don't
you speak English. lady?

297
00:17:10.446 --> 00:17:12.449
Uh. look. maybe...

298
00:17:12.532 --> 00:17:13.825
(IMITATING)
Uh. maybe...

299
00:17:13.909 --> 00:17:16.453
What the child is
trying to say is...

300
00:17:16.537 --> 00:17:19.915
(MOCKING) Maybe if I shrug my shoulders
and move around my hands like this.

301
00:17:19.957 --> 00:17:22.709
maybe people
will think I know what I'm talking about.

302
00:17:22.792 --> 00:17:25.127
Look. it's obvious that
the kid's unbalanced.

303
00:17:25.212 --> 00:17:26.797
I mean. I knew that
from the start.

304
00:17:26.880 --> 00:17:29.007
I was playing
devil's advocate.

305
00:17:29.091 --> 00:17:30.634
Devil. you know...

306
00:17:30.717 --> 00:17:34.137
Anyway. on behalf of
myself and the agency.

307
00:17:34.221 --> 00:17:39.351
this child is going to be removed from
this orphanage as soon as possible.

308
00:17:39.434 --> 00:17:42.229
Well. hurry the hell up.
I'm not getting any younger.

309
00:17:42.479 --> 00:17:43.647
(RINGING BELL)

310
00:17:47.401 --> 00:17:49.278
(CAT MEOWING)

311
00:17:59.162 --> 00:18:02.666
There's Ed and Sally
and little Joey going into the Whites'.

312
00:18:02.708 --> 00:18:04.168
There must
be a party.

313
00:18:05.460 --> 00:18:07.838
Look at her dress.
That's a new...

314
00:18:08.505 --> 00:18:10.841
I've looked all over
for shoes like that.

315
00:18:10.924 --> 00:18:12.593
Wonder why we
weren't invited.

316
00:18:12.676 --> 00:18:16.013
Same reason we weren't invited
to the Reynolds'. the Burkes' or the Cursons'.

317
00:18:16.054 --> 00:18:19.349
You can't go to a kids'
party if you don't have a kid.

318
00:18:19.391 --> 00:18:21.685
Being a parent is power.

319
00:18:21.727 --> 00:18:24.396
and once you're in that circle. you wanna
just keep everyone else out.

320
00:18:24.479 --> 00:18:27.316
Flo. being a parent
is about sharing.

321
00:18:27.357 --> 00:18:30.569
It's about a mom.
a dad and a kid.

322
00:18:30.652 --> 00:18:32.738
Except. there isn't
going to be a kid. Ben.

323
00:18:32.821 --> 00:18:35.741
It's just you
and me forever.

324
00:18:40.954 --> 00:18:42.998
Florence.
why can't we adopt?

325
00:18:43.040 --> 00:18:44.249
We've been
through this.

326
00:18:44.333 --> 00:18:47.336
I know. but we have
so much love to give.

327
00:18:47.377 --> 00:18:49.546
Why waste it on
these stupid pets?

328
00:18:49.588 --> 00:18:51.882
They are not stupid!

329
00:18:51.924 --> 00:18:53.509
Hello! Hello!

330
00:18:53.550 --> 00:18:55.344
Think of it this way.

331
00:18:55.385 --> 00:18:58.263
All those mothers had
to make do with what nature gave them.

332
00:18:58.347 --> 00:19:03.060
But you and I. we get to pick out our kid.
It'll be like shopping.

333
00:19:03.143 --> 00:19:04.770
-Shopping?
-Uh-huh.

334
00:19:05.854 --> 00:19:09.900
But the neighbors will know we've adopted.
What'll they say?

335
00:19:09.942 --> 00:19:13.153
The neighbors?
What they'll say is... They'll say. "Look.

336
00:19:13.237 --> 00:19:15.113
"there's Ben and Flo Healy

337
00:19:15.197 --> 00:19:18.492
"going out to yet another
birthday party with their new son.

338
00:19:18.575 --> 00:19:20.494
"Isn't he adorable?

339
00:19:20.577 --> 00:19:25.249
"And look at how fantastic
Flo looks in her new dress!

340
00:19:25.290 --> 00:19:28.126
"Where did she ever get a
bag to match those shoes?"

341
00:19:28.210 --> 00:19:32.548
And then they'll say.
"Let's invite that Healy family over for dinner."

342
00:19:32.589 --> 00:19:35.300
Oh. Ben. dinners!

343
00:19:35.384 --> 00:19:36.510
(CAT SHRIEKING)

344
00:19:36.635 --> 00:19:37.761
Okay. let's get a kid.

345
00:19:38.303 --> 00:19:41.431
All right. hurry up. students.
Five more minutes for your pen pals.

346
00:19:41.473 --> 00:19:44.434
and then we have to work
on our times tables.

347
00:19:45.978 --> 00:19:51.275
GIRL: Dear Queen Elizabeth. how is England?
It must be nice to be a queen.

348
00:19:51.316 --> 00:19:54.194
BOY: Dear Bishop Tutu.
how are you?

349
00:19:54.278 --> 00:19:58.323
I am fine. I hope everything's
going well with your marching.

350
00:19:58.407 --> 00:20:00.826
JUNIOR: Dear Bow Tie Killer.
how's prison?

351
00:20:00.909 --> 00:20:05.455
There's a nice picture of you on the front page
that I'm gonna add to my collection.

352
00:20:05.497 --> 00:20:09.585
Even though we've never met.
I feel we have a lot in common.

353
00:20:09.626 --> 00:20:11.503
Nobody understands us.

354
00:20:11.587 --> 00:20:15.841
I'm still wearing a bow tie.
so I can look just like you.

355
00:20:15.924 --> 00:20:18.802
After all these letters.
I've got good news.

356
00:20:18.886 --> 00:20:21.305
I'm getting out.
Isn't that great?

357
00:20:21.388 --> 00:20:24.474
Your number one fan. Junior.

358
00:20:33.859 --> 00:20:35.068
Smoke.

359
00:20:45.537 --> 00:20:49.666
Sir. sorry to disturb you
but this letter came for you.

360
00:20:54.630 --> 00:20:56.006
Read this to me.

361
00:20:57.591 --> 00:20:59.927
Hey. it's a
letter from J.R.

362
00:21:00.010 --> 00:21:01.261
Yeah?

363
00:21:01.345 --> 00:21:03.931
Someday we're gonna
meet up on the outside.

364
00:21:04.014 --> 00:21:06.975
We're gonna do
some serious damage.

365
00:21:07.017 --> 00:21:09.394
"Good news.
I'm getting out."

366
00:21:09.478 --> 00:21:12.022
What? He's getting paroled?

367
00:21:12.105 --> 00:21:14.691
They gotta be out
of their minds!

368
00:21:14.775 --> 00:21:17.486
You know that guy?
He's crazier than I am.

369
00:21:17.528 --> 00:21:20.239
Chill. The warden!

370
00:21:20.322 --> 00:21:22.533
Well. well. if it isn't
our model prisoner.

371
00:21:22.616 --> 00:21:26.703
looking so pretty today
in his little bow tie.

372
00:21:26.787 --> 00:21:28.872
Hey. warden. catch!

373
00:21:30.040 --> 00:21:31.250
(SCREAMING)

374
00:21:32.543 --> 00:21:34.378
You know. honey.
I hope I'm not rushing you.

375
00:21:34.419 --> 00:21:36.547
We can always let
nature take its course.

376
00:21:36.630 --> 00:21:39.883
Nature screwed us over.
Let's give commerce a try.

377
00:21:42.719 --> 00:21:44.972
Okay. let's see
what I can do here.

378
00:21:45.055 --> 00:21:46.515
You want a kid
you could love.

379
00:21:46.557 --> 00:21:48.267
I'll put you on
the waiting list.

380
00:21:48.350 --> 00:21:51.311
You should have a kid
in about seven years.

381
00:21:51.395 --> 00:21:52.563
Seven years?

382
00:21:52.604 --> 00:21:53.897
Unless...

383
00:21:53.939 --> 00:21:58.068
Nah. nah. just...
I didn't say a word. I did not say a word.

384
00:21:58.110 --> 00:22:01.321
(STAMMERING) No. what?
What were you gonna say?

385
00:22:01.405 --> 00:22:07.369
Well. I really put my foot in my mouth this
time but. I don't know. I like you two.

386
00:22:07.411 --> 00:22:09.496
Kill me. I like
the two of you.

387
00:22:09.580 --> 00:22:12.040
And when I like two people.
I want to help them out.

388
00:22:12.082 --> 00:22:15.460
That's just my nature.
I want to help out people that I like.

389
00:22:15.544 --> 00:22:16.920
(LAUGHING)

390
00:22:17.004 --> 00:22:21.091
Just this morning I came
upon a seven-year-old.

391
00:22:21.925 --> 00:22:26.054
Smart as a tack. a little rambunctious
but weren't we all at that age?

392
00:22:26.096 --> 00:22:27.598
(LAUGHING)

393
00:22:27.639 --> 00:22:30.601
Oh. I think I even have
a photo here for you.

394
00:22:31.894 --> 00:22:34.688
FLO: Oh. he does look very
presentable in that little bow tie.

395
00:22:34.771 --> 00:22:36.481
Adorable!

396
00:22:36.565 --> 00:22:37.774
But I don't know.

397
00:22:37.816 --> 00:22:41.111
Seven is rather old. I wanted people to
think I had the baby myself.

398
00:22:41.195 --> 00:22:46.033
That's understandable. A lot of women feel
that way. You want a cute little infant.

399
00:22:46.116 --> 00:22:48.911
One that will start screaming
in the middle of the night.

400
00:22:48.952 --> 00:22:51.705
and you'll have to stumble
downstairs in the dark

401
00:22:51.788 --> 00:22:54.458
and change his smelly
and soiled diapers.

402
00:22:54.583 --> 00:22:57.419
And you know. you'll do your
housework. and you'll eat chocolates

403
00:22:57.461 --> 00:23:01.215
and take care of the kid and
you'll put on 50 or 60 pounds.

404
00:23:01.298 --> 00:23:03.342
-No diapers?
-Hey. you know. you like to sleep late.

405
00:23:03.425 --> 00:23:05.511
There'd be no baby
waking you up in the morning.

406
00:23:05.594 --> 00:23:11.308
We could skip all that baby junk and move
right into the good stuff. like

407
00:23:11.642 --> 00:23:14.728
parties and more parties!

408
00:23:14.811 --> 00:23:17.022
I could be president
of the PTA by September!

409
00:23:17.105 --> 00:23:19.316
And it would be nice
for Fuzzball to have someone to play with.

410
00:23:19.399 --> 00:23:21.485
Yes!
Fuzzball's our cat.

411
00:23:21.568 --> 00:23:25.489
I can't believe it.
Junior. he loves cats.

412
00:23:25.572 --> 00:23:27.783
Do you hear that?
Let's do it. Let's do it.

413
00:23:28.742 --> 00:23:31.787
Mr. Peabody.
you've got yourself a deal.

414
00:23:31.828 --> 00:23:33.664
And you've got yourself a kid.

415
00:23:41.338 --> 00:23:44.258
Here he comes.
Flo. that's our son.

416
00:23:46.343 --> 00:23:47.761
Can you believe it?
Oh. my God.

417
00:23:47.845 --> 00:23:49.513
I can't believe it.
That's our boy.

418
00:23:49.555 --> 00:23:51.557
Oh. he's very handsome.

419
00:23:51.640 --> 00:23:53.433
I'll be the envy
of the neighborhood.

420
00:23:53.517 --> 00:23:55.561
They look like
a couple of yahoos.

421
00:23:55.644 --> 00:23:57.187
(CHUCKLING)

422
00:23:59.773 --> 00:24:01.024
BEN: Hi!

423
00:24:02.192 --> 00:24:03.777
I think I'm gonna cry.

424
00:24:03.861 --> 00:24:06.947
JUNIOR: You ever seen
a grown man wear so much blue?

425
00:24:07.030 --> 00:24:09.700
Hey there.
little buddy.

426
00:24:09.783 --> 00:24:11.869
I'm Ben. This is Flo.

427
00:24:11.910 --> 00:24:13.370
Put it there. partner.

428
00:24:13.453 --> 00:24:16.623
Hi. My name's Junior.
My favorite color's blue. What's yours?

429
00:24:18.292 --> 00:24:21.503
Blue! My favorite color's
blue. too. Can you believe...

430
00:24:21.545 --> 00:24:24.923
He's perfect.
He's wonderful. Come here.

431
00:24:25.007 --> 00:24:28.427
Thank you.
Sisters. goodbye. Goodbye. kids.

432
00:24:28.510 --> 00:24:31.180
Bye. everybody.
Don't forget to write.

433
00:24:34.725 --> 00:24:36.810
(LOCKS BOLTING)

434
00:24:37.728 --> 00:24:39.688
BEN: Hey. we must have gotten
the pick of the litter.

435
00:24:39.730 --> 00:24:41.982
Look. everyone's come
out to see him off.

436
00:24:43.734 --> 00:24:45.736
(ALL CHEERING)

437
00:25:02.544 --> 00:25:05.339
BEN: Here we are.
Isn't this exciting?

438
00:25:05.422 --> 00:25:09.760
All right. everybody out.
Everybody out. This is gonna be so great.

439
00:25:09.801 --> 00:25:13.347
Okay. now. everybody
over by the house.

440
00:25:13.430 --> 00:25:16.225
This is Junior's first
day at his new home.

441
00:25:16.266 --> 00:25:18.727
Okay. I want everyone over.
Come on. Come on.

442
00:25:18.769 --> 00:25:20.687
Junior. put your suitcase
down right here.

443
00:25:20.771 --> 00:25:22.981
Darling. I want
you to hug him.

444
00:25:23.065 --> 00:25:26.068
A lot of teeth.
I want everybody to be happy. all right?

445
00:25:26.109 --> 00:25:28.987
Smile and say.
"Cheese doodles!"

446
00:25:29.071 --> 00:25:30.781
-Cheese doodles!
-Cheese doodles!

447
00:25:30.864 --> 00:25:32.658
That's great.
That's terrific.

448
00:25:33.325 --> 00:25:36.578
So. how come you adopted me?
How come you just didn't have a baby?

449
00:25:38.413 --> 00:25:39.998
Well. gee...

450
00:25:40.832 --> 00:25:43.752
You know. with a baby.
you never know what you're getting.

451
00:25:43.794 --> 00:25:47.422
It could be a dud.
But with you. see. there's no surprise.

452
00:25:47.464 --> 00:25:49.258
Mr. Peabody told us
how terrific you are.

453
00:25:49.299 --> 00:25:50.342
He did?

454
00:25:50.425 --> 00:25:55.180
Sure. He said that you were voted
"Most Popular Orphan" two years in a row.

455
00:25:55.264 --> 00:25:57.140
That was
smart of him.

456
00:25:58.976 --> 00:26:00.519
BEN: Here we go.

457
00:26:00.602 --> 00:26:04.356
Wow! This is
a great house.

458
00:26:04.439 --> 00:26:07.359
And we're going to keep
it neat and clean. aren't we?

459
00:26:13.073 --> 00:26:15.242
I hope you guys
are insured.

460
00:26:15.492 --> 00:26:16.743
(HISSING)

461
00:26:16.827 --> 00:26:20.163
Oh. and you have a cat.
Here. kitty. kitty.

462
00:26:20.998 --> 00:26:22.165
(FUZZBALL MEOWING)

463
00:26:22.249 --> 00:26:25.294
No. no. Junior.
Make nice with kitty.

464
00:26:25.335 --> 00:26:27.212
-(FUZZBALL SHRIEKING)
-Only pet her this way.

465
00:26:27.296 --> 00:26:29.173
I've never seen
Fuzzball act like that.

466
00:26:29.256 --> 00:26:30.340
(POLLY SQUAWKING)

467
00:26:30.382 --> 00:26:33.385
Junior. come here.
I want you to meet Polly. Come here.

468
00:26:34.094 --> 00:26:37.472
Polly. say hello
to Junior.

469
00:26:37.514 --> 00:26:39.183
Hello. Hello.

470
00:26:39.224 --> 00:26:41.768
Is that the only
word he knows?

471
00:26:41.852 --> 00:26:44.188
Yes. son. Come on.
I want to show you the rest of the house.

472
00:26:44.229 --> 00:26:45.355
POLLY: Uh-oh.

473
00:26:47.065 --> 00:26:48.275
Do I get my own bed?

474
00:26:48.358 --> 00:26:51.028
Your own bed? Junior. this is the big time.
You get your own room.

475
00:26:51.111 --> 00:26:52.154
Wow!

476
00:26:52.196 --> 00:26:53.614
I hope you like clowns.

477
00:26:55.449 --> 00:26:57.618
(CLOWNS LAUGHING)

478
00:26:58.535 --> 00:27:01.079
JUNIOR: Oh. my God.
They're retarded.

479
00:27:02.414 --> 00:27:04.249
So. what do you think.
big guy?

480
00:27:04.333 --> 00:27:07.544
Well. there sure are
a lot of clowns.

481
00:27:07.586 --> 00:27:08.712
(BOTH LAUGHING)

482
00:27:08.795 --> 00:27:10.047
(DOORBELL RINGING)

483
00:27:10.756 --> 00:27:13.175
That must be your new grandpa.
Now. Junior. you stay right here.

484
00:27:13.217 --> 00:27:15.469
We'll give old gramps
a big surprise. okay?

485
00:27:15.844 --> 00:27:17.054
Shh.

486
00:27:24.728 --> 00:27:27.147
Dad. are we
glad to see you. Come on in.

487
00:27:27.231 --> 00:27:30.484
So what's this big surprise
you dragged me over here for?

488
00:27:30.567 --> 00:27:33.654
Well. Dad.
here's a hint.

489
00:27:35.572 --> 00:27:38.784
Oh. my God!

490
00:27:38.867 --> 00:27:40.202
Finally!

491
00:27:40.244 --> 00:27:41.787
(LAUGHING)

492
00:27:41.870 --> 00:27:44.831
You and Flo cooked up
a cute little kid for my campaign.

493
00:27:46.041 --> 00:27:50.128
You know. I thought you were getting fatter.
Mama. When's my little grandson due?

494
00:27:50.212 --> 00:27:52.339
-Fatter?
-No. Dad. No. no.

495
00:27:52.422 --> 00:27:54.925
Florence is not
gonna have a baby.

496
00:27:55.259 --> 00:27:57.594
You rascal. you!

497
00:27:57.636 --> 00:27:59.847
You followed my advice
and took your sperm to somebody

498
00:27:59.930 --> 00:28:01.306
who knows what
to do with it. huh?

499
00:28:01.390 --> 00:28:02.558
(LAUGHING)

500
00:28:02.599 --> 00:28:04.059
A surrogate mother.

501
00:28:04.101 --> 00:28:05.811
Listen. tell me something.

502
00:28:05.894 --> 00:28:08.939
do you make out with a cup
or you get to bump a real live one?

503
00:28:08.981 --> 00:28:10.023
(CHUCKLING)

504
00:28:10.107 --> 00:28:12.442
No. no.
Dad. we adopted.

505
00:28:12.901 --> 00:28:14.987
Are you insane?

506
00:28:16.113 --> 00:28:19.116
I thought you'd be happy.
Come on.

507
00:28:19.157 --> 00:28:22.077
Happy? You don't know
what you're letting yourself in for.

508
00:28:22.119 --> 00:28:24.121
BIG BEN: Dopehead mothers.
Garbage blood.

509
00:28:24.162 --> 00:28:26.623
For all you know.
his parents may have met in a loony bin.

510
00:28:26.665 --> 00:28:28.041
They might even
be Democrats.

511
00:28:28.125 --> 00:28:30.043
He's a beautiful kid. Dad.
Relax.

512
00:28:30.127 --> 00:28:32.796
Once you meet him.
you'll love him like your very own.

513
00:28:32.838 --> 00:28:38.051
I would like to proudly present the newest
member of the Healy family. Junior.

514
00:28:39.094 --> 00:28:40.971
No! Junior!

515
00:28:41.513 --> 00:28:43.432
BIG BEN: Hey! Now.
that's a $1.000 coat!

516
00:28:43.473 --> 00:28:45.142
Junior. are you in here?

517
00:28:45.184 --> 00:28:46.894
Junior! Junior!

518
00:28:46.977 --> 00:28:48.145
(JUNIOR COUGHING)

519
00:28:48.228 --> 00:28:51.023
Oh. my God!
It's the devil.

520
00:28:51.106 --> 00:28:52.524
-Buddy. are you okay?
-Yeah.

521
00:28:52.608 --> 00:28:53.609
(COUGHING)

522
00:28:53.650 --> 00:28:54.902
Just a little smoky.

523
00:28:56.528 --> 00:29:00.908
Oh. look. here's the problem.
This clown must have shorted out.

524
00:29:00.991 --> 00:29:04.494
Sparks were coming out of his nose.
I was so scared.

525
00:29:04.828 --> 00:29:06.872
Nah. the little punk
is lying.

526
00:29:06.955 --> 00:29:08.498
Dad! Dad!

527
00:29:08.582 --> 00:29:12.753
Well. I hope you kept the damn receipt.
You got one bad seed there.

528
00:29:12.836 --> 00:29:14.463
BEN: Would you keep your voice down?
He could hear you.

529
00:29:14.505 --> 00:29:16.006
You'll hurt his feelings.
It was just an accident.

530
00:29:16.048 --> 00:29:17.090
(FUZZBALL MEOWING)

531
00:29:17.174 --> 00:29:18.926
BIG BEN: Accident. my ass!
Get rid of him.

532
00:29:19.009 --> 00:29:20.677
BEN: Forget it. Dad.
We've made our decision.

533
00:29:20.719 --> 00:29:24.181
Okay. but it's the last time
I set foot in this house.

534
00:29:24.264 --> 00:29:25.432
(SCREAMING)

535
00:29:26.850 --> 00:29:29.770
BEN: My God! Dad! Stop!

536
00:29:31.021 --> 00:29:32.523
(SIREN WAILING)

537
00:29:35.359 --> 00:29:37.611
Come on. boys.
Get back.

538
00:29:37.694 --> 00:29:39.863
WOMAN: Oh.
what's happening?

539
00:29:39.905 --> 00:29:41.740
BIG BEN: The kid.

540
00:29:41.823 --> 00:29:45.744
Get rid of that kid.
Get rid of him.

541
00:29:45.827 --> 00:29:47.120
Easy!

542
00:29:48.121 --> 00:29:49.706
Get rid of that kid.

543
00:29:57.089 --> 00:29:59.842
Poor Fuzzball.
She'll never be the same.

544
00:30:00.509 --> 00:30:05.055
Are you...
Is that all you can think of. is your stupid cat?

545
00:30:05.722 --> 00:30:08.934
What about the fact
that Father's on his way to the hospital?

546
00:30:09.017 --> 00:30:12.187
Or that Junior's had such
a traumatic first day?

547
00:30:12.229 --> 00:30:15.816
Did you stop and think
about the poor boy? He must feel horrible.

548
00:30:18.485 --> 00:30:20.988
JUNIOR: Yeah. but this
might make me feel better.

549
00:30:22.239 --> 00:30:24.408
50. 60.

550
00:30:24.449 --> 00:30:26.577
70. 80...

551
00:30:30.414 --> 00:30:31.415
Oh.

552
00:30:32.291 --> 00:30:34.459
I see a furry bunny.

553
00:30:36.170 --> 00:30:41.508
And the furry bunny is running
through delicate white snowflakes.

554
00:30:41.592 --> 00:30:43.677
He's lying.
That's not what he sees.

555
00:30:43.760 --> 00:30:47.181
I'm sorry.
I'm conducting an examination.

556
00:30:47.264 --> 00:30:48.640
Now what do
you see. Martin?

557
00:30:48.724 --> 00:30:51.476
I see a meadow.
Pink flowers.

558
00:30:51.560 --> 00:30:53.812
He's lying again.
How can he see pink?

559
00:30:53.896 --> 00:30:57.107
It's a black and white picture.
There is no pink.

560
00:30:57.191 --> 00:30:58.734
Warden. if you don't
stop interrupting.

561
00:30:58.775 --> 00:31:00.777
I am going to have
to ask you to leave.

562
00:31:00.861 --> 00:31:02.571
Well. there is no pink.

563
00:31:05.073 --> 00:31:07.618
I see white
fluffy clouds...

564
00:31:07.659 --> 00:31:08.869
No. you don't!

565
00:31:08.952 --> 00:31:10.287
You see murder!
You see guts!

566
00:31:10.329 --> 00:31:11.914
My patient has the right
to a private examination.

567
00:31:11.955 --> 00:31:13.457
You see those seven bodies!

568
00:31:13.498 --> 00:31:15.209
-I'm going to ask you to leave.
-Those damn liberal laws!

569
00:31:15.292 --> 00:31:17.294
Don't you understand?
He sees blood!

570
00:31:17.336 --> 00:31:18.962
No. that's
what you see.

571
00:31:22.132 --> 00:31:24.301
I am so sorry
about that. Martin.

572
00:31:25.594 --> 00:31:30.641
Now. let's get back
to our examination. shall we?

573
00:31:30.682 --> 00:31:32.226
What do you
see in this one?

574
00:31:32.309 --> 00:31:33.852
I see

575
00:31:34.770 --> 00:31:36.396
blood!

576
00:31:42.986 --> 00:31:44.821
Hey. Doc. how did it go
with the star patient?

577
00:31:44.863 --> 00:31:49.159
Oh. that guy. There's a few
bricks missing from his building.

578
00:31:58.877 --> 00:32:00.337
(FLOOR CREAKING)

579
00:32:03.841 --> 00:32:05.425
(GROWLING)

580
00:32:06.593 --> 00:32:07.594
(HISSING)

581
00:32:07.678 --> 00:32:08.679
(SHRIEKING)

582
00:32:21.191 --> 00:32:22.776
Hey. what are you doing?

583
00:32:22.860 --> 00:32:24.111
Nothing.

584
00:32:25.153 --> 00:32:26.989
Gosh. what happened here?

585
00:32:27.030 --> 00:32:30.450
I was looking for some paper
to write a get-well note to Big Ben.

586
00:32:31.952 --> 00:32:36.874
Gee. that's very thoughtful.
Junior. but these are Mom's private drawers.

587
00:32:36.915 --> 00:32:40.878
You shouldn't go in there. It's where she
keeps her needlepoint and crocheting.

588
00:32:52.431 --> 00:32:57.311
I'm really sorry. Mr. Healy.
I was scared being all alone in my room.

589
00:32:59.188 --> 00:33:02.733
Of course. I understand
why you're scared.

590
00:33:02.816 --> 00:33:05.569
This is your first night
in your new home.

591
00:33:05.611 --> 00:33:09.406
It's gonna take some
getting used to. isn't it?

592
00:33:10.115 --> 00:33:13.327
You know. Junior.
I've got to confess. I'm a little scared myself.

593
00:33:13.410 --> 00:33:16.246
This is my first night
being a dad.

594
00:33:16.288 --> 00:33:18.248
Well. you'll learn
quick enough.

595
00:33:18.290 --> 00:33:20.584
Learn? Learn what?

596
00:33:20.626 --> 00:33:24.046
What it's like to be a dad.
Then you'll get rid of me.

597
00:33:25.714 --> 00:33:29.176
Get rid of you?
Junior. we're never gonna get rid of you.

598
00:33:29.259 --> 00:33:31.094
You're here forever.

599
00:33:31.136 --> 00:33:33.847
The two of us.
we're gonna do everything together.

600
00:33:33.931 --> 00:33:37.559
We'll ride bikes.
go fishing. play catch.

601
00:33:37.601 --> 00:33:40.103
I really want
to be a good dad.

602
00:33:40.145 --> 00:33:42.940
I want to be a great dad.
and you know what?

603
00:33:42.981 --> 00:33:47.611
I will never be too busy to sit down and listen
to what's on my son's mind

604
00:33:47.653 --> 00:33:49.905
over a nice cup
of hot cocoa.

605
00:33:57.287 --> 00:34:00.958
Hey. sleepyhead.
You all ready to go camping?

606
00:34:01.166 --> 00:34:02.167
Huh?

607
00:34:02.584 --> 00:34:05.462
I was planning
on watching cartoons.

608
00:34:05.546 --> 00:34:07.172
Don't be such a noodle.

609
00:34:07.256 --> 00:34:09.632
When I was your age.
my father.

610
00:34:09.675 --> 00:34:13.219
your grandfather.
was always too busy to ever take me camping.

611
00:34:13.303 --> 00:34:15.264
You are a lucky duck.

612
00:34:15.304 --> 00:34:16.556
Ben!

613
00:34:17.683 --> 00:34:18.809
Bring him.

614
00:34:19.476 --> 00:34:21.143
Come here. Junior.
I want you to meet someone.

615
00:34:21.228 --> 00:34:24.356
Mrs. Henderson.
And little Miss Lucy.

616
00:34:25.983 --> 00:34:27.568
What a nice surprise.

617
00:34:27.650 --> 00:34:30.821
Well. we heard about
your little accident

618
00:34:30.904 --> 00:34:34.408
and we thought this
fruitcake might cheer you up.

619
00:34:34.491 --> 00:34:35.826
Thank you.

620
00:34:36.869 --> 00:34:40.246
I would like you
to meet my son. Junior.

621
00:34:41.039 --> 00:34:42.541
Pleased to meet you. ladies.

622
00:34:42.623 --> 00:34:47.295
Oh. my! He's a perfect
little gentleman. Isn't he. Lucy?

623
00:34:47.337 --> 00:34:49.005
He's so big.

624
00:34:49.047 --> 00:34:51.507
Yesterday they didn't
even have a kid

625
00:34:51.592 --> 00:34:55.596
and now they have
a seven-year-old. That's gross.

626
00:34:56.138 --> 00:34:57.973
I don't want him
at my party.

627
00:34:58.015 --> 00:35:00.267
(CHUCKLING) Lucy.

628
00:35:00.350 --> 00:35:06.231
But. Mother. he dresses like the
man that cremated Uncle Leo.

629
00:35:06.315 --> 00:35:09.193
Lucy's turning six this week.

630
00:35:09.276 --> 00:35:12.446
But I don't think
we'll have a clown this year.

631
00:35:13.697 --> 00:35:14.990
Or balloons.

632
00:35:15.824 --> 00:35:17.242
Or ice cream.

633
00:35:18.327 --> 00:35:19.411
(SIGHING)

634
00:35:19.494 --> 00:35:22.873
I'm having a birthday
party. Saturday.

635
00:35:22.956 --> 00:35:25.792
I think it would
be nice if you came.

636
00:35:30.130 --> 00:35:32.341
Well. we'll see you
Saturday at 2:00.

637
00:35:32.382 --> 00:35:33.425
We'll be there.

638
00:35:33.509 --> 00:35:34.676
Come on. Lucy.
get in the car.

639
00:35:34.718 --> 00:35:35.969
FLO: Thanks for
the fruitcake.

640
00:35:36.053 --> 00:35:38.180
I'll return the
lovely platter.

641
00:35:38.222 --> 00:35:39.389
BEN: Thanks again.

642
00:35:39.431 --> 00:35:41.683
This is wonderful.
We have finally been accepted.

643
00:35:41.725 --> 00:35:43.268
This parent crap
is really paying off.

644
00:35:43.352 --> 00:35:45.812
I can't believe it.
It's a dream come true. A birthday party.

645
00:35:45.896 --> 00:35:48.065
Now we're actually going
camping with our own son.

646
00:35:48.148 --> 00:35:50.484
Not me. pal. I'm going to the mall
to buy a dress for the party.

647
00:35:50.567 --> 00:35:51.777
Give me some money.

648
00:35:51.860 --> 00:35:55.614
Oh. Does that mean
you're not going camping with us?

649
00:35:55.697 --> 00:35:56.740
Not on your life.

650
00:35:56.782 --> 00:35:58.075
Oh. okay.

651
00:35:59.284 --> 00:36:02.329
Junior? This gives me an idea.
You know something?

652
00:36:02.412 --> 00:36:05.999
I don't see why my son
shouldn't be getting his very own allowance.

653
00:36:06.083 --> 00:36:07.417
What do you
say about that?

654
00:36:07.459 --> 00:36:08.836
All right!

655
00:36:08.919 --> 00:36:13.090
Okay. Now. this is going to give you a good
opportunity to learn to manage money.

656
00:36:14.091 --> 00:36:16.593
A buck? How do you
manage a buck?

657
00:36:17.261 --> 00:36:21.265
Come on. Mr. Molasses.
Let's go. We're late.

658
00:36:26.520 --> 00:36:27.771
(BIRD CAWING)

659
00:36:29.147 --> 00:36:31.108
Neat. bears!

660
00:36:31.149 --> 00:36:32.192
(CHUCKLING)

661
00:36:32.276 --> 00:36:36.196
Don't worry. buddy.
Bears rarely attack unless provoked.

662
00:36:36.655 --> 00:36:40.200
Now. let's keep our
eyes peeled for campsite number 32.

663
00:36:40.284 --> 00:36:42.744
That's the one Roy
reserved especially for us.

664
00:36:44.454 --> 00:36:48.792
Nice spot your friend
reserved especially for us. Mr. Healy.

665
00:36:49.376 --> 00:36:53.297
This is nature. huh?
The sky. the trees...

666
00:36:53.338 --> 00:36:54.548
The toilets.

667
00:36:54.631 --> 00:36:57.718
Hey. you guys. You're not gonna
see the sunset from over there.

668
00:36:57.801 --> 00:37:00.637
Come on over and
watch on our river bank. Come on.

669
00:37:00.721 --> 00:37:02.347
I'd tell him to shove it.
Mr. Healy.

670
00:37:02.431 --> 00:37:03.432
(BIRD SQUAWKING)

671
00:37:03.473 --> 00:37:05.517
It's no big deal.
More important.

672
00:37:05.601 --> 00:37:08.395
why don't you call me Dad?
I'd really like that.

673
00:37:08.478 --> 00:37:11.190
I want to go home
and watch TV.

674
00:37:11.273 --> 00:37:17.154
TV? What's TV compared to the call of the
wild bobolink in that spruce over there?

675
00:37:17.654 --> 00:37:19.823
(FARTING)

676
00:37:19.865 --> 00:37:22.117
That's a pretty big bobolink!

677
00:37:22.242 --> 00:37:25.120
ALL: (SINGING)
Old MacDonald had a farm

678
00:37:25.329 --> 00:37:27.664
E-I-E-I-O

679
00:37:27.831 --> 00:37:28.999
(SINGING CONTINUING)

680
00:37:29.041 --> 00:37:31.293
(ROY AND BEN CHATTERING)

681
00:37:31.460 --> 00:37:32.753
(LAUGHING)

682
00:37:33.295 --> 00:37:35.380
Hey. kids. the wienies
are almost done.

683
00:37:35.464 --> 00:37:36.798
-Yeah.
-All right.

684
00:37:36.840 --> 00:37:39.426
I don't believe this.

685
00:37:39.510 --> 00:37:42.846
JUNIOR: Those are Roy's kids.
They're sharing a brain.

686
00:37:42.888 --> 00:37:45.015
The one on the end
has it today.

687
00:37:47.392 --> 00:37:51.605
Little Ben. get in here.
Inside. Get in here. Come on.

688
00:37:53.524 --> 00:37:56.652
So. how does it feel.
your first night camping with your son?

689
00:37:56.693 --> 00:37:59.154
Oh. Roy. it's great!
It's a dream. It's a dream come true.

690
00:37:59.238 --> 00:38:02.407
Sure. forget the fact that you had to go
into kid emporium and buy one.

691
00:38:02.491 --> 00:38:06.036
Big deal! I mean. we can't all
produce six perfect little angels.

692
00:38:06.078 --> 00:38:07.329
like me and Harriet.

693
00:38:07.371 --> 00:38:10.749
Well. I only got one.
but he's one in a million.

694
00:38:11.166 --> 00:38:13.043
-(ROARING)
-Oh. God!

695
00:38:13.126 --> 00:38:15.295
Oh! Gee. Roy.

696
00:38:15.379 --> 00:38:17.381
Oh. it's gonna give the kids
a big scare. isn't it?

697
00:38:17.464 --> 00:38:19.550
-Well. you got me.
-Wait a minute.

698
00:38:19.591 --> 00:38:21.176
-I got something else for you.
-They'll eat this up.

699
00:38:21.218 --> 00:38:24.179
I can't wait to see
their little faces light up with excitement.

700
00:38:24.221 --> 00:38:26.056
It's so real.
Where'd you get this?

701
00:38:26.098 --> 00:38:30.561
Little Ben.
now that you're a father. try this on for size.

702
00:38:30.686 --> 00:38:31.687
Huh?

703
00:38:33.313 --> 00:38:35.524
(CHUCKLING)

704
00:38:35.566 --> 00:38:37.234
Gee. thanks. Roy.

705
00:38:38.735 --> 00:38:41.113
CHILDREN: (SINGING)
The monkey thought it was all in fun

706
00:38:41.196 --> 00:38:43.365
Pop goes the weasel

707
00:38:43.407 --> 00:38:48.203
A penny for a spool of thread
A penny for a needle

708
00:38:48.245 --> 00:38:52.749
That's the way the money goes
Pop goes the weasel

709
00:38:52.791 --> 00:38:54.001
-All right.
-All right.

710
00:38:54.084 --> 00:38:56.545
-What do we do now?
-Let's tell ghost stories.

711
00:38:56.587 --> 00:38:58.088
Let's roast marshmallows.

712
00:38:58.172 --> 00:38:59.715
Let's light
a forest fire.

713
00:38:59.756 --> 00:39:02.467
Don't you know it's bad
to light forest fires?

714
00:39:02.551 --> 00:39:03.927
That's the whole point.

715
00:39:04.011 --> 00:39:06.263
I'm gonna tell
my daddy on you.

716
00:39:06.305 --> 00:39:08.640
-I'm gonna tell.
-I'm gonna tell.

717
00:39:08.724 --> 00:39:10.601
Let's give him
the silent treatment.

718
00:39:10.642 --> 00:39:12.311
Yeah. just ignore him.

719
00:39:14.188 --> 00:39:16.106
Ignore this.

720
00:39:16.481 --> 00:39:17.941
(ALL SCREAMING)

721
00:39:18.025 --> 00:39:19.401
Oh. gross!

722
00:39:24.364 --> 00:39:27.326
This outdoor life is gonna be
just the ticket for Junior.

723
00:39:27.409 --> 00:39:29.286
I think he's really
gonna blossom out here.

724
00:39:29.328 --> 00:39:31.663
We sure do enjoy it.

725
00:39:31.747 --> 00:39:36.502
I bet you've never
been camping before. It's so much fun.

726
00:39:36.585 --> 00:39:42.591
There's singing. marshmallows
and all sorts of stupid humans to scare.

727
00:39:44.218 --> 00:39:45.219
(GROWLING)

728
00:39:45.302 --> 00:39:49.723
Row. row. row your boat
Gently down the stream

729
00:39:49.806 --> 00:39:54.311
Merrily. merrily. merrily. merrily
Life is but a dream

730
00:39:55.479 --> 00:39:56.480
(GROWLING)

731
00:39:58.941 --> 00:40:00.692
(ALL SCREAMING)

732
00:40:04.488 --> 00:40:06.031
Roy. you devil.

733
00:40:10.160 --> 00:40:14.289
What's the matter. kids?
You're afraid of a measly little bear?

734
00:40:14.331 --> 00:40:15.707
BEN: He's not so bad.

735
00:40:15.832 --> 00:40:19.127
(WHISPERING) This is great.
This is great. Roy.

736
00:40:20.170 --> 00:40:21.338
(CHUCKLING)

737
00:40:21.421 --> 00:40:24.508
Let's see if he's ticklish.
Is Mr. Bear ticklish?

738
00:40:24.550 --> 00:40:25.717
Coochie-coochie!

739
00:40:26.718 --> 00:40:28.178
Coochie-coochie!

740
00:40:28.679 --> 00:40:30.556
That was close. You...

741
00:40:30.681 --> 00:40:32.349
(GROWLING)

742
00:40:33.851 --> 00:40:36.186
Roy? Roy!

743
00:40:36.270 --> 00:40:38.021
Help!

744
00:40:38.063 --> 00:40:41.358
Help! Help!

745
00:40:50.993 --> 00:40:52.870
Stay here. Stay here.

746
00:40:52.911 --> 00:40:54.288
Stay here.

747
00:40:55.205 --> 00:40:56.832
Where'd he go?

748
00:40:56.874 --> 00:40:58.208
I think it left.

749
00:40:58.250 --> 00:40:59.251
(GROWLING)

750
00:41:20.480 --> 00:41:23.150
He must have learned it
from the tourists.

751
00:41:25.485 --> 00:41:26.486
(CHUCKLING)

752
00:41:42.085 --> 00:41:43.212
Roy!

753
00:41:43.253 --> 00:41:44.838
(JUNIOR LAUGHING)

754
00:41:50.093 --> 00:41:54.431
I can't get it out of my head that Junior was
responsible for the camping thing.

755
00:41:54.515 --> 00:41:57.184
You should have seen him laughing. Flo.
He was laughing his head off.

756
00:41:57.267 --> 00:41:59.436
Why don't you just lock
him in his room tonight?

757
00:41:59.520 --> 00:42:03.106
Well. it says here that children often
misbehave just to get attention.

758
00:42:03.190 --> 00:42:06.026
And we should resort
to discipline only when other forms

759
00:42:06.109 --> 00:42:08.820
of positive re-enforcement
have failed.

760
00:42:09.613 --> 00:42:10.906
Up yours.
Up yours.

761
00:42:10.948 --> 00:42:12.115
(LAUGHING)

762
00:42:12.199 --> 00:42:13.408
Reinforce that.

763
00:42:13.534 --> 00:42:14.576
(SQUAWKING)

764
00:42:14.618 --> 00:42:15.786
Dickhead.

765
00:42:20.666 --> 00:42:24.253
Mrs. Henderson.
your home is lovely.

766
00:42:24.294 --> 00:42:25.754
Call me Marion.

767
00:42:25.796 --> 00:42:27.840
Marion.
This is fabulous.

768
00:42:27.923 --> 00:42:30.175
There's nothing more wonderful
than children playing.

769
00:42:30.259 --> 00:42:32.719
hearing the sound
of the little voices laughing.

770
00:42:32.803 --> 00:42:33.804
Excuse me.

771
00:42:33.887 --> 00:42:36.348
But Marion. did you see
Junior's little outfit?

772
00:42:36.640 --> 00:42:38.559
FLO: Isn't he just precious?

773
00:42:43.647 --> 00:42:44.815
(BALLOON POPPING)

774
00:42:45.357 --> 00:42:48.569
Well. so Big Ben's
means big business.

775
00:42:48.652 --> 00:42:50.904
Junior. I got some
buttons for the kids

776
00:42:50.988 --> 00:42:53.073
and some bumper stickers
for their bikes.

777
00:42:53.156 --> 00:42:54.825
Now. why don't you do
your grandfather a big favor

778
00:42:54.867 --> 00:42:57.494
and pass them out among
your little friends. huh?

779
00:42:57.536 --> 00:42:59.037
What for?

780
00:42:59.997 --> 00:43:03.876
What for? For 10 bucks.
that's what's for.

781
00:43:04.459 --> 00:43:06.003
Sure. Grandpa.

782
00:43:07.004 --> 00:43:08.255
Kids. huh?

783
00:43:14.094 --> 00:43:16.638
Hmm. Hmm.

784
00:43:21.810 --> 00:43:25.647
Hey. put that down.
That's mine. These are all my presents.

785
00:43:25.689 --> 00:43:27.191
I was only looking at it.

786
00:43:27.232 --> 00:43:31.153
Well. you're gonna break it.
Get away from it. It's mine.

787
00:43:31.195 --> 00:43:32.279
Who's that?

788
00:43:32.362 --> 00:43:36.116
He's a new boy.
but he can't play with us. He's got cooties.

789
00:43:36.200 --> 00:43:39.369
He's not even a real kid.
He's adopted.

790
00:43:39.411 --> 00:43:41.163
GIRL: Ew! Gross!

791
00:43:41.205 --> 00:43:46.126
All right. boys and girls.
Come on out. Time for the magic show.

792
00:43:46.210 --> 00:43:47.628
All right!

793
00:43:48.253 --> 00:43:49.421
(FABRIC RIPPING)

794
00:43:49.505 --> 00:43:51.798
-You can't come out.
-Why not?

795
00:43:51.882 --> 00:43:54.009
'Cause I said so.
It's my party

796
00:43:54.051 --> 00:43:58.055
and I get to say who can watch
my magic show and who can't.

797
00:44:15.239 --> 00:44:17.449
Why aren't you outside
watching the magic show?

798
00:44:17.533 --> 00:44:19.284
Clowns are dumb.

799
00:44:19.368 --> 00:44:21.745
It's tough being
left out. isn't it?

800
00:44:25.165 --> 00:44:26.875
If I were to give
you something.

801
00:44:26.917 --> 00:44:30.003
would you promise to take
very good care of it?

802
00:44:36.927 --> 00:44:40.848
My grandfather gave this
to me just before he died.

803
00:44:40.931 --> 00:44:42.266
What is it?

804
00:44:43.684 --> 00:44:47.938
It's a prune. hardened.
It's a hardened prune.

805
00:44:48.021 --> 00:44:50.148
Grandfather became
a little senile toward the end.

806
00:44:50.232 --> 00:44:52.568
He thought it
resembled Roosevelt.

807
00:44:53.151 --> 00:44:58.448
But the important thing
is that it's a bond between two people.

808
00:45:01.118 --> 00:45:03.537
I've kept it in my pocket
for almost 30 years.

809
00:45:03.620 --> 00:45:06.164
Ben. get over here.
I want you to meet the Hofsteders.

810
00:45:06.248 --> 00:45:08.000
Coming. sweetheart.

811
00:45:08.083 --> 00:45:10.460
I know you'll take
as good a care of it as I have.

812
00:45:10.544 --> 00:45:12.004
Ben. move it!

813
00:45:20.137 --> 00:45:22.431
LUCY: You can't come
to my magic show.

814
00:45:24.349 --> 00:45:26.476
JUNIOR: I had some
magic of my own.

815
00:45:56.381 --> 00:45:57.591
(SCREAMING)

816
00:46:53.021 --> 00:46:54.857
(SCREAMING)

817
00:47:40.986 --> 00:47:45.282
JUNIOR: Perhaps this was the one step
too far. This could be a problem.

818
00:47:45.365 --> 00:47:46.533
I think we've
got a problem.

819
00:47:46.617 --> 00:47:48.285
Oh. you think
we've got a problem?

820
00:47:48.368 --> 00:47:49.870
Well. you want to know
what I think?

821
00:47:49.953 --> 00:47:52.122
I think we should get rid
of the kid and buy a new cat.

822
00:47:52.164 --> 00:47:53.916
Flo. you're not
making any sense.

823
00:47:53.957 --> 00:47:57.836
Oh. you want to make sense?
Why don't you show him who's boss?

824
00:47:57.920 --> 00:47:59.755
Here. Be a man.

825
00:48:05.969 --> 00:48:08.639
Please. God. I'm so sorry
for what I've done.

826
00:48:08.722 --> 00:48:11.308
I won't ever do it again.
I promise.

827
00:48:11.350 --> 00:48:15.103
And I don't ever want to cause
Mr. Healy any trouble.

828
00:48:15.145 --> 00:48:18.148
He's the only one that's
ever been nice to me.

829
00:48:21.068 --> 00:48:23.445
Please don't spank me.
Mr. Healy.

830
00:48:24.613 --> 00:48:28.325
Boy. Junior. I don't want to.
but you're gonna have to be punished.

831
00:48:28.367 --> 00:48:31.787
So. I'm gonna take
back your allowance.

832
00:48:32.496 --> 00:48:34.289
The whole buck?

833
00:48:34.331 --> 00:48:36.834
That's right.
Now. just hand it over.

834
00:48:43.924 --> 00:48:46.385
JUNIOR: I wonder if
he's got change for a 20?

835
00:48:53.308 --> 00:48:57.479
Okay. I think you
better go right to bed.

836
00:48:57.521 --> 00:49:01.149
Just use this time
to think about what you've done

837
00:49:01.191 --> 00:49:03.944
and what you're going to do.
Understand?

838
00:49:08.073 --> 00:49:11.660
I hope you've learned
a lesson. Good night.

839
00:49:14.037 --> 00:49:17.499
JUNIOR: What is this guy?
Nice or something?

840
00:49:17.875 --> 00:49:20.043
(HORN BLARING)

841
00:49:30.512 --> 00:49:32.347
-Can I help you?
-Yeah. fill her up.

842
00:49:39.021 --> 00:49:40.898
Smiley Pies!

843
00:49:41.732 --> 00:49:44.985
I ain't had a
Smiley Pie in 15 years.

844
00:50:19.770 --> 00:50:23.774
MAN: (OVER PA) Now. Cold River's
favorite son. Big Ben Healy.

845
00:50:23.857 --> 00:50:26.401
(CROWD CHEERING)

846
00:50:26.443 --> 00:50:29.029
BIG BEN: First of all.
I'd like to thank everyone

847
00:50:29.112 --> 00:50:31.323
who's supporting me
in my race for mayor.

848
00:50:31.406 --> 00:50:32.616
(ALL CHEERING)

849
00:50:33.951 --> 00:50:35.369
This is the
Founder's Day game.

850
00:50:35.452 --> 00:50:38.121
It really doesn't matter
who wins or loses.

851
00:50:38.205 --> 00:50:40.374
Just so long as
Big Ben wins for mayor.

852
00:50:40.791 --> 00:50:41.792
(ALL LAUGHING)

853
00:50:42.334 --> 00:50:45.963
And when you little fellas
hit one out. and that scoreboard lights up.

854
00:50:46.004 --> 00:50:48.090
I want you
to remember Big Ben.

855
00:50:58.016 --> 00:51:00.769
ANNOUNCER: We go to the
seventh inning tied three to three.

856
00:51:05.524 --> 00:51:08.485
(CROWD CHATTERING)

857
00:51:14.324 --> 00:51:18.161
BEN: All right. shake it off. Now. somebody's
gonna have to pinch-hit for Andy.

858
00:51:18.245 --> 00:51:21.331
Okay. buddy. this is it.
Your big moment.

859
00:51:21.373 --> 00:51:22.791
Who. me?

860
00:51:22.833 --> 00:51:26.044
Of course you. Junior.
Come on. I need you to bat.

861
00:51:26.128 --> 00:51:28.005
Get up. grab a helmet.

862
00:51:28.881 --> 00:51:30.382
Get a bat. that's a boy.

863
00:51:30.465 --> 00:51:33.844
But I don't know
how to play baseball.

864
00:51:33.927 --> 00:51:36.972
Well. now is as good
a time as any to learn.

865
00:51:37.014 --> 00:51:38.182
But what happens if...

866
00:51:38.223 --> 00:51:40.684
It doesn't matter
what happens.

867
00:51:40.726 --> 00:51:44.688
The important thing is that you stand up
there and take your cuts. okay?

868
00:51:44.730 --> 00:51:47.858
Remember. I'll be proud
of you no matter how you do. All right. buddy.

869
00:51:47.900 --> 00:51:51.778
Are you out of your mind. for God's sakes.
putting that little monster in the game?

870
00:51:51.862 --> 00:51:53.697
I'm on a campaign here.
I have to look good.

871
00:51:53.739 --> 00:51:57.117
Junior'll do just fine. Dad.
You can do it. buddy. You can do it. Come on.

872
00:51:57.201 --> 00:51:59.244
Nice little tie.
moose breath.

873
00:51:59.328 --> 00:52:01.955
Bet you sell
a lot of Girl Scout cookies wearing that.

874
00:52:02.039 --> 00:52:03.415
ROY: No batter. Cort.

875
00:52:03.498 --> 00:52:04.541
(KIDS LAUGHING)

876
00:52:04.583 --> 00:52:06.251
He's cute. isn't he?

877
00:52:08.003 --> 00:52:09.213
BOY: Come on.

878
00:52:10.756 --> 00:52:12.174
Strike one.

879
00:52:14.218 --> 00:52:17.971
You know. if that kid wasn't adopted.
I'd swear he was your real son.

880
00:52:18.972 --> 00:52:22.434
Who are you. sweetie pie? You weren't on the
team the last time we beat you.

881
00:52:22.518 --> 00:52:25.145
The guy I'm staying
with is the coach.

882
00:52:25.479 --> 00:52:28.649
Oh. you mean that big dork
who buys everyone ice cream.

883
00:52:29.191 --> 00:52:30.859
He is not a dork.

884
00:52:30.901 --> 00:52:33.612
Watch the pitcher.
not the catcher. buddy. Come on!

885
00:52:36.615 --> 00:52:38.033
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

886
00:52:47.417 --> 00:52:50.337
My new car! Oh. my God!

887
00:52:50.838 --> 00:52:52.756
Shake it off. okay?
Just tighten up that grip. all right?

888
00:52:52.840 --> 00:52:53.841
-All right. meet the ball.
-Yeah.

889
00:52:53.924 --> 00:52:55.926
Whatever you do.
hold onto the bat. okay?

890
00:52:55.968 --> 00:52:57.427
-Yeah.
-Come on. boy!

891
00:52:57.511 --> 00:53:01.598
Good idea. Yeah.
hold on to the bat.

892
00:53:02.015 --> 00:53:04.852
Son of dork. son of dork!

893
00:53:04.935 --> 00:53:06.603
(CHANTING) Son of dork!

894
00:53:06.645 --> 00:53:08.146
Son of dork!

895
00:53:08.230 --> 00:53:09.356
Son of dork!

896
00:53:09.439 --> 00:53:10.983
-KIDS: Son of dork!
-Oh. no.

897
00:53:11.066 --> 00:53:12.609
Son of dork!

898
00:53:12.693 --> 00:53:13.944
Son of dork!

899
00:53:14.027 --> 00:53:15.362
Son of dork!

900
00:53:15.445 --> 00:53:17.030
Son of dork!

901
00:53:17.114 --> 00:53:18.699
Son of dork!

902
00:53:25.414 --> 00:53:27.082
Drop the bat. son.

903
00:53:31.837 --> 00:53:33.005
No. that's no good.

904
00:53:33.088 --> 00:53:35.048
Hey! You can't do that.

905
00:53:35.632 --> 00:53:36.800
Whoa!

906
00:53:36.884 --> 00:53:37.885
(THUDDING)

907
00:53:40.137 --> 00:53:43.432
Drop the bat. Junior!
Are you nuts?

908
00:53:47.019 --> 00:53:48.520
-(THUDDING)
-ALL: Whoa!

909
00:54:00.490 --> 00:54:02.618
Come on. little dork.
I got something for you.

910
00:54:06.163 --> 00:54:07.164
(GROANING)

911
00:54:09.082 --> 00:54:13.003
Touchdown! Touchdown!
Touchdown! Touchdown!

912
00:54:18.258 --> 00:54:23.931
Touchdown! Touchdown! Touchdown!
Touchdown! Touchdown! Touchdown!

913
00:54:26.767 --> 00:54:28.519
We've adopted Satan.

914
00:54:29.061 --> 00:54:31.522
I don't know what
you could've been thinking about.

915
00:54:31.563 --> 00:54:32.898
We've done everything
we can for you.

916
00:54:32.981 --> 00:54:35.526
Now. you wait right here.
I'm gonna get the priest.

917
00:54:39.196 --> 00:54:43.700
Hello. Mr. Healy.
Remember me? You sold me a canteen.

918
00:54:43.784 --> 00:54:46.411
Boy. did we have
a great camping trip!

919
00:54:46.495 --> 00:54:49.665
I caught three fish.
My dad was really proud.

920
00:54:49.706 --> 00:54:51.542
Blow it out your ass.

921
00:54:54.711 --> 00:54:56.547
FLO: Junior. Junior!

922
00:54:57.464 --> 00:54:59.466
Get back here.
you little heathen.

923
00:55:00.843 --> 00:55:01.885
Junior!

924
00:55:01.927 --> 00:55:03.929
Where are you.
you little creep?

925
00:55:21.822 --> 00:55:25.242
Bless me. Father.
for I have sinned. Father? Father?

926
00:55:27.077 --> 00:55:29.162
Father. I'm at the
end of my rope.

927
00:55:29.246 --> 00:55:31.290
It's about my kid.
He's a real problem.

928
00:55:31.373 --> 00:55:34.084
He does the most terrible
things. hideous things.

929
00:55:34.168 --> 00:55:38.046
(STAMMERING) My father hates him.
My wife hates him. Everybody hates him.

930
00:55:38.088 --> 00:55:41.300
Well. everybody except me.
And I've had it with him myself.

931
00:55:41.383 --> 00:55:44.761
God! I've failed. Father.
The kid hates me.

932
00:55:44.845 --> 00:55:47.431
It's time I faced up
to what I do have to do.

933
00:55:47.514 --> 00:55:49.892
I'm gonna take him
back to the orphanage.

934
00:55:49.933 --> 00:55:53.770
No. no. you don't want to do that!
That's the worst thing you could do!

935
00:56:08.994 --> 00:56:10.078
Can I call you back
in five minutes?

936
00:56:10.120 --> 00:56:11.330
He's all yours.

937
00:56:11.413 --> 00:56:12.873
Ben. Flo. can we
discuss this?

938
00:56:12.956 --> 00:56:14.458
There is nothing to discuss.

939
00:56:14.499 --> 00:56:17.002
We're signing him back
over to you right now.

940
00:56:17.085 --> 00:56:19.296
Bad parents make bad children!

941
00:56:19.338 --> 00:56:21.840
Oh. so. now I'm a bad parent
just because I hate my kid?

942
00:56:21.924 --> 00:56:23.550
There is something
very strange about that boy.

943
00:56:23.634 --> 00:56:25.677
He is twisted. And you're not
gonna palm him off on us.

944
00:56:25.761 --> 00:56:27.304
You took him.
He's yours.

945
00:56:27.346 --> 00:56:29.264
That's because
you conned us into him.

946
00:56:29.306 --> 00:56:31.600
What am I supposed to do
with the little creep?

947
00:56:31.642 --> 00:56:34.478
He's already been
returned 30 times.

948
00:56:34.561 --> 00:56:36.855
Well. this makes 31. Charlie.

949
00:56:36.939 --> 00:56:40.150
Okay. Mr. and Mrs. "We don't care
about brown hair and brown eyes.

950
00:56:40.192 --> 00:56:43.654
"We just want to take him into our home and
let him play with our disgusting cat."

951
00:56:43.737 --> 00:56:46.281
Hold it. hold it.
Stop. Stop. wait.

952
00:56:46.323 --> 00:56:50.285
Well. what are we talking about?
30? 30 times?

953
00:56:50.327 --> 00:56:52.913
Flo. did you hear that?
He's been returned...

954
00:56:52.996 --> 00:56:55.874
My God. this is a human being
we're talking about.

955
00:56:55.958 --> 00:56:58.377
Don't you give me that
human-being crap. That kid's a monster!

956
00:56:58.460 --> 00:57:02.381
Flo. don't you see? We're doing what
everybody else has done to this child.

957
00:57:02.464 --> 00:57:04.842
I mean. it's easy
to give up on a kid.

958
00:57:04.883 --> 00:57:06.176
Damn straight it is.

959
00:57:06.218 --> 00:57:09.304
But isn't that what's wrong
with the world today?

960
00:57:09.346 --> 00:57:11.515
I mean. everybody's looking
for the easy way out.

961
00:57:11.557 --> 00:57:16.395
(STAMMERING) They're hoping
that their problems will just go away.

962
00:57:16.895 --> 00:57:21.275
But problems don't
just go. Flo. you know?

963
00:57:21.358 --> 00:57:26.196
So. the question before us is what are we
gonna do with our little problem child?

964
00:57:26.613 --> 00:57:28.532
I'll tell you
what we're gonna do.

965
00:57:28.615 --> 00:57:32.286
Something that no one's
ever done for him ever before.

966
00:57:32.369 --> 00:57:34.413
We're gonna love him. Flo.

967
00:57:34.830 --> 00:57:37.207
Oh. yes. we're gonna
love him when he's bad.

968
00:57:37.291 --> 00:57:39.334
We're gonna love him even
harder when he's worse.

969
00:57:39.376 --> 00:57:43.130
Until one day
he's gonna crack and say.

970
00:57:43.547 --> 00:57:47.384
"Hey. these folks
really do love me.

971
00:57:48.218 --> 00:57:50.429
"They ain't gonna quit on me.

972
00:57:50.512 --> 00:57:52.931
"I don't have to
be bad anymore.

973
00:57:53.807 --> 00:57:58.020
"What the hay!
I can be President of the United States!"

974
00:57:58.562 --> 00:58:01.899
President of the United States?
Are you brain-damaged?

975
00:58:01.982 --> 00:58:04.484
Junior's gonna be a convict
before he's in third grade.

976
00:58:04.568 --> 00:58:05.569
Shh!

977
00:58:06.028 --> 00:58:08.322
Junior? Son?

978
00:58:09.406 --> 00:58:10.824
Junior. unlock the door.

979
00:58:10.908 --> 00:58:13.577
You said you were
gonna keep me forever.

980
00:58:14.745 --> 00:58:18.916
I am. I'm sorry.
I just made a mistake. Trust me.

981
00:58:18.957 --> 00:58:22.127
We're not gonna take you
back to the orphanage.

982
00:58:22.211 --> 00:58:23.504
I don't believe you.

983
00:58:23.587 --> 00:58:27.716
You only pretended to be my friend.
You're just like all the others.

984
00:58:28.926 --> 00:58:30.135
Junior?

985
00:58:30.719 --> 00:58:32.471
Now. come on. son.

986
00:58:34.097 --> 00:58:36.808
You moron!
You left the keys in the car.

987
00:58:37.601 --> 00:58:41.313
Hey. he can drive!
Boy. that's great!

988
00:58:41.897 --> 00:58:45.734
Look at you handle this baby!
I'm so proud of you. son!

989
00:58:47.444 --> 00:58:50.656
Junior! Junior! Hold it!

990
00:58:53.450 --> 00:58:55.661
MAN: Get out of the way.
you jerk!

991
00:58:56.286 --> 00:58:57.871
Left! Turn left!

992
00:58:58.914 --> 00:59:01.124
Right. Junior!
Right. Junior!

993
00:59:01.708 --> 00:59:02.960
Watch it!

994
00:59:05.045 --> 00:59:07.005
No!

995
00:59:08.799 --> 00:59:11.969
No. no. no. No. no. no...
Don't touch that! Don't touch...

996
00:59:13.470 --> 00:59:15.055
Junior!

997
00:59:24.064 --> 00:59:25.607
No!

998
00:59:26.775 --> 00:59:28.151
Watch out!

999
00:59:54.636 --> 00:59:55.971
(PHONE RINGING)

1000
01:00:03.520 --> 01:00:04.521
Hello?

1001
01:00:05.439 --> 01:00:07.691
Ben? Jim O'Connor.
Are you sitting down?

1002
01:00:08.233 --> 01:00:09.318
Yes.

1003
01:00:09.818 --> 01:00:10.903
Bad news. Ben.

1004
01:00:10.986 --> 01:00:14.781
Your father cleaned out your bank account
to pay for the damage to his store.

1005
01:00:14.865 --> 01:00:18.160
Look. I know nothing can make up for the
loss of your life savings. but...

1006
01:00:18.202 --> 01:00:19.369
Ben?

1007
01:00:30.923 --> 01:00:33.383
JUNIOR: Uh-oh!
He's lost it now.

1008
01:00:34.885 --> 01:00:36.970
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1009
01:00:47.898 --> 01:00:49.399
All right!

1010
01:00:55.072 --> 01:00:56.907
Private business.

1011
01:00:56.990 --> 01:00:58.075
Hi.

1012
01:00:58.909 --> 01:01:02.746
Get out of my way. kid.
I'm looking for J.R.

1013
01:01:02.829 --> 01:01:04.540
That's me. Junior.

1014
01:01:08.210 --> 01:01:11.672
I don't have time
for this crap. kid.

1015
01:01:11.755 --> 01:01:16.677
Now. the guy I'm looking for is an ex-con
and he's as mean as a rattlesnake.

1016
01:01:16.760 --> 01:01:20.097
That's me. dummy!
I sent you all those letters.

1017
01:01:20.180 --> 01:01:25.978
Man. I drove a thousand miles
to hang out with a seven-year-old?

1018
01:01:26.311 --> 01:01:28.146
I'm gonna be eight
in two weeks.

1019
01:01:28.230 --> 01:01:30.023
Don't count on it.

1020
01:01:34.486 --> 01:01:40.325
Mr. Healy. Mrs. Healy. I'd like you to meet
the greatest guy in the whole wide world.

1021
01:01:40.409 --> 01:01:41.910
Martin. uh...

1022
01:01:43.620 --> 01:01:45.789
Uncle Marty!
Yeah. Uncle Marty!

1023
01:01:45.873 --> 01:01:47.958
Marty. this is
Mr. and Mrs. Healy.

1024
01:01:48.041 --> 01:01:52.171
And that's the $3.000 stereo system
and the console TV.

1025
01:01:52.254 --> 01:01:54.631
How wonderful!
An uncle!

1026
01:01:54.673 --> 01:01:56.967
You absolutely must
stay the night.

1027
01:01:57.050 --> 01:02:00.846
It is so wonderful to meet the uncle
of our darling little Junior.

1028
01:02:00.929 --> 01:02:03.724
Did you hear that?
Uncle Marty.

1029
01:02:03.807 --> 01:02:05.642
We've gotta treat
this guy like royalty.

1030
01:02:05.684 --> 01:02:07.811
We've gotta make him think
that Junior's an angel.

1031
01:02:07.895 --> 01:02:11.023
We can't let him leave
without taking that little brat with him.

1032
01:02:11.481 --> 01:02:14.026
Everybody just loves Junior.

1033
01:02:14.109 --> 01:02:15.819
Would you believe
that for pocket money.

1034
01:02:15.903 --> 01:02:19.031
he helps some of
the older residents with their groceries.

1035
01:02:19.114 --> 01:02:20.657
Isn't that right. Ben?

1036
01:02:20.741 --> 01:02:22.451
(BEN MUTTERING)

1037
01:02:22.492 --> 01:02:27.581
But if only he had a blood relative taking care
of him. someone with a natural tie.

1038
01:02:27.664 --> 01:02:29.416
Like an uncle!

1039
01:02:29.499 --> 01:02:30.834
More meatloaf. Marty?

1040
01:02:30.876 --> 01:02:31.919
Yeah.

1041
01:02:32.002 --> 01:02:33.670
I'll get you some.

1042
01:02:34.004 --> 01:02:36.256
JUNIOR: This guy is
just so appealing.

1043
01:02:37.299 --> 01:02:39.051
I'll give you a hand.

1044
01:02:42.596 --> 01:02:44.932
Your nephew is such a
delight around the house.

1045
01:02:45.015 --> 01:02:48.143
He's always cleaning and
tidying up after all of us.

1046
01:02:48.185 --> 01:02:50.687
Perfect for a single
man living alone.

1047
01:02:50.771 --> 01:02:52.856
Are you a bachelor. Marty?

1048
01:02:55.150 --> 01:02:58.695
I ain't been with
a woman in 15 years.

1049
01:02:58.737 --> 01:03:00.948
Well. women just love
single male parents.

1050
01:03:01.031 --> 01:03:05.661
I mean. if you had a kid like Junior.
the women would be flocking over you.

1051
01:03:15.295 --> 01:03:16.547
(FLO PANTING)

1052
01:03:16.588 --> 01:03:18.340
Did you say 15 years?

1053
01:03:20.801 --> 01:03:22.052
Wait.

1054
01:03:25.055 --> 01:03:26.390
(UTENSILS CLATTERING)

1055
01:03:26.431 --> 01:03:27.808
MARTIN: Stop it!

1056
01:03:28.809 --> 01:03:31.103
(MARTIN GROANING)

1057
01:04:01.758 --> 01:04:04.803
Hey. let me show you
all the stuff I brought for our trip.

1058
01:04:04.887 --> 01:04:09.933
I got my ammo. There's guns.
hand grenades. and even dynamite.

1059
01:04:14.438 --> 01:04:16.398
These are toys.

1060
01:04:16.440 --> 01:04:19.693
What are you jerking me around for?
This is kiddies' stuff!

1061
01:04:21.778 --> 01:04:25.991
Hey. what did you do that for?
Don't we need supplies?

1062
01:04:26.074 --> 01:04:29.369
What are you talking about?
I'm not working with you.

1063
01:04:29.453 --> 01:04:33.457
But I thought we were gonna be partners.
I thought you liked me.

1064
01:04:33.540 --> 01:04:35.959
Hey. I don't like no one.

1065
01:04:36.585 --> 01:04:37.961
I work alone.

1066
01:04:40.881 --> 01:04:46.011
Goodbye. Junior! Goodbye. Flo!
Oh. I am so sad to see you go.

1067
01:04:46.094 --> 01:04:50.307
$100.000? Ha!
You can keep them!

1068
01:04:50.390 --> 01:04:53.435
Good morning!
Hello. sunshine!

1069
01:04:55.354 --> 01:04:57.940
I thought this was supposed
to be our honeymoon.

1070
01:04:57.981 --> 01:05:01.610
You said you loved me.
You called me your little kumquat.

1071
01:05:01.652 --> 01:05:04.404
This is our honeymoon.
you moron.

1072
01:05:04.488 --> 01:05:07.157
Moron? Moron?

1073
01:05:07.658 --> 01:05:10.452
I went to Radcliffe.
I'm not just some uneducated bimbo

1074
01:05:10.494 --> 01:05:12.746
you can tie up and do
whatever you want with.

1075
01:05:12.829 --> 01:05:14.540
-You shut up!
-I will not shut up!

1076
01:05:14.623 --> 01:05:18.377
FLO: Let me out of here.
Do something. you stupid piece of...

1077
01:05:18.460 --> 01:05:20.128
You're gonna regret this.

1078
01:05:20.170 --> 01:05:21.421
You're gonna have
to open this trunk.

1079
01:05:21.505 --> 01:05:25.342
I'm gonna be waiting and when I'm done with
you. you're gonna be singing falsetto!

1080
01:05:25.717 --> 01:05:29.096
Here's Daddy!

1081
01:05:32.057 --> 01:05:33.851
Goodbye. Junior!

1082
01:05:34.518 --> 01:05:37.855
Adiós! Hasta luego!

1083
01:05:39.022 --> 01:05:40.524
Sayonara!

1084
01:05:41.859 --> 01:05:43.485
Yeah!

1085
01:05:45.153 --> 01:05:47.739
Yes. that's very
creative. Junior.

1086
01:05:49.199 --> 01:05:51.159
Yeah. right on the money.

1087
01:06:11.680 --> 01:06:13.140
He liked me.

1088
01:06:14.516 --> 01:06:17.477
All this time
he actually liked me.

1089
01:06:29.907 --> 01:06:32.034
Vote for Big Ben.
Here. read this.

1090
01:06:36.205 --> 01:06:40.167
You can't go in. Your father's making
a television appearance for his campaign.

1091
01:06:42.503 --> 01:06:45.005
Dad? Dad.
I gotta talk to you.

1092
01:06:45.088 --> 01:06:48.342
Oh. what the hell are you doing here?
I'm about to go on the air.

1093
01:06:48.425 --> 01:06:50.344
Florence and Junior
have been kidnapped.

1094
01:06:50.427 --> 01:06:52.054
-Five minutes. Mr. Healy.
-All right. All right.

1095
01:06:52.095 --> 01:06:53.222
I need $100.000.

1096
01:06:53.263 --> 01:06:54.765
Are you insane?

1097
01:06:54.806 --> 01:06:57.976
That kid is a monster
and your wife is the original pain in the ass.

1098
01:06:58.060 --> 01:07:00.395
This is the best damn thing
that could've happened to you.

1099
01:07:00.437 --> 01:07:02.231
Dad. are you gonna lend
me the money or not?

1100
01:07:02.272 --> 01:07:04.149
No. I'm not gonna
lend it to you.

1101
01:07:04.233 --> 01:07:08.654
You work for me. remember. I know
what you get. You're a damn credit risk.

1102
01:07:10.030 --> 01:07:12.074
Okay. then I quit
as your son.

1103
01:07:12.115 --> 01:07:13.992
All right. Just get the
hell out of here. huh?

1104
01:07:14.076 --> 01:07:16.119
I got a goddamn
campaign to win.

1105
01:07:16.203 --> 01:07:19.289
Your campaign.
the one thing you do care about.

1106
01:07:21.416 --> 01:07:23.585
Hey. Dad. why don't you
go ahead and tell the voters

1107
01:07:23.627 --> 01:07:25.838
what you really plan
on doing with this town?

1108
01:07:25.921 --> 01:07:27.965
I don't give
a rat's ass for the voters.

1109
01:07:28.048 --> 01:07:30.425
Well. I guess we're ready
with that live feed

1110
01:07:30.467 --> 01:07:32.094
from Big Ben Healy
on the campaign trail.

1111
01:07:32.135 --> 01:07:34.054
That's why I'm a success
and you're not.

1112
01:07:34.137 --> 01:07:37.057
America for the Americans.
You believe that nonsense?

1113
01:07:37.140 --> 01:07:38.475
You're stupider
than I thought.

1114
01:07:38.559 --> 01:07:41.270
I'd sell my soul to the Japanese
if they'd make me an offer.

1115
01:07:41.311 --> 01:07:42.354
(BIG BEN LAUGHING)

1116
01:07:42.437 --> 01:07:45.941
And as for you. don't come sucking round
me if you want something.

1117
01:07:45.983 --> 01:07:48.819
The only thing you'll
get from me is this.

1118
01:07:52.239 --> 01:07:54.116
(PHONE RINGING)

1119
01:08:04.251 --> 01:08:06.712
(PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

1120
01:08:07.212 --> 01:08:08.255
Hello?

1121
01:08:08.589 --> 01:08:09.673
You got the money?

1122
01:08:10.215 --> 01:08:11.925
Uh. yeah.

1123
01:08:12.259 --> 01:08:14.887
Good. Bring it
to the circus.

1124
01:08:15.679 --> 01:08:18.098
I'll be waiting
at the tiger cage.

1125
01:08:20.600 --> 01:08:23.020
Roy. I need your car.

1126
01:08:23.060 --> 01:08:25.314
Hey. forget about it. Chester.
We're going hunting.

1127
01:08:25.354 --> 01:08:26.398
So am I.

1128
01:08:26.481 --> 01:08:29.859
Hey. Little Ben. you can't borrow it.
We're all packed up and ready to go.

1129
01:08:29.902 --> 01:08:32.362
What are you doing?
Get comfortable in there.

1130
01:08:32.404 --> 01:08:33.738
You're not going
anywhere. buddy.

1131
01:08:33.822 --> 01:08:37.367
Hey! Hey!
Just wait a minute.

1132
01:08:37.408 --> 01:08:39.703
Oh. great. Well. the joke's over.
Come on back.

1133
01:08:39.745 --> 01:08:42.038
Yeah. What do you
think you're doing?

1134
01:08:42.122 --> 01:08:43.290
Hey!

1135
01:08:45.417 --> 01:08:46.417
GIRL: Hey. you can't...

1136
01:08:46.502 --> 01:08:49.212
ROY: Hey! Hey.
get back here. you!

1137
01:08:49.880 --> 01:08:50.881
Hey!

1138
01:08:52.883 --> 01:08:55.051
GIRL: What is he doing?
ROY: Get back here!

1139
01:08:56.428 --> 01:08:59.348
Gee. I've never been
to the circus before.

1140
01:08:59.389 --> 01:09:01.350
I'd sure like to
try a swizzle dog.

1141
01:09:01.390 --> 01:09:03.185
Yeah. well.
I hate circuses.

1142
01:09:03.227 --> 01:09:06.522
Nothing worse than
a bunch of clowns trying to make you laugh.

1143
01:09:07.606 --> 01:09:10.067
(HONKING)

1144
01:09:16.406 --> 01:09:18.200
Look. a giraffe!

1145
01:09:18.242 --> 01:09:19.910
Look. a fist!

1146
01:09:19.993 --> 01:09:20.993
(HONKING)

1147
01:09:24.372 --> 01:09:25.582
Clowns.

1148
01:09:26.834 --> 01:09:30.002
FLO: Help! Help!
Let me out of here.

1149
01:09:30.087 --> 01:09:33.090
I know you're out there.
Get help!

1150
01:09:33.173 --> 01:09:36.385
Why isn't anybody doing anything?
I know you're out there.

1151
01:09:36.426 --> 01:09:38.053
I can hear you breathing.

1152
01:09:44.059 --> 01:09:46.103
Hey. Martin. let's go
see the bearded lady.

1153
01:09:46.144 --> 01:09:48.939
No. I've seen too many
of them in prison.

1154
01:09:48.981 --> 01:09:50.941
Now. stop bugging me
or you're gonna get hurt.

1155
01:09:51.024 --> 01:09:53.277
What did you say.
you bow-tied freak?

1156
01:09:53.318 --> 01:09:55.779
Nobody hurts my boy.
Now let him go!

1157
01:09:56.905 --> 01:10:01.577
Forget it. big daddy.
Now. this is my show. I'm calling the shots.

1158
01:10:01.618 --> 01:10:04.955
Okay. we make a switch
on the count of three.

1159
01:10:05.831 --> 01:10:08.584
You toss the money
and I release Junior.

1160
01:10:08.667 --> 01:10:09.835
Fine.

1161
01:10:10.419 --> 01:10:13.130
One. two. three.

1162
01:10:13.797 --> 01:10:14.965
BEN: Hey. what are you...

1163
01:10:15.048 --> 01:10:16.633
-Sucker!
-Give me the boy.

1164
01:10:16.717 --> 01:10:19.595
Why? He doesn't wanna go with you.
He wants to go with me.

1165
01:10:20.637 --> 01:10:24.183
How about it. kid?
We'll go on a crime spree.

1166
01:10:24.266 --> 01:10:26.101
We'll terrorize
the whole state.

1167
01:10:26.143 --> 01:10:29.771
We'll eat Smiley Pies until we drop.
What do you say?

1168
01:10:33.275 --> 01:10:36.612
Come on. let's have some kicks.
Tell-a me.

1169
01:10:36.653 --> 01:10:38.155
Tell-a me.

1170
01:10:38.238 --> 01:10:40.866
Yeah. kicks. good idea.

1171
01:10:41.575 --> 01:10:43.035
(GRUNTING)

1172
01:10:46.371 --> 01:10:48.665
I'll tear you apart.
you little brat!

1173
01:10:48.749 --> 01:10:50.542
Not while I'm around.

1174
01:10:51.001 --> 01:10:52.503
Run. Junior. run!

1175
01:10:53.420 --> 01:10:54.755
My money!

1176
01:11:01.345 --> 01:11:02.679
Hold it!

1177
01:11:03.597 --> 01:11:08.185
ANNOUNCER: The astounding
Aslanian Family Tumblers!

1178
01:11:08.519 --> 01:11:11.021
(CROWD CHEERING)

1179
01:11:23.200 --> 01:11:26.370
(YELLING IN
FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

1180
01:11:39.049 --> 01:11:40.676
Excuse me. lady!

1181
01:11:46.431 --> 01:11:48.058
(SCREAMING)

1182
01:11:56.733 --> 01:11:58.402
I'll get you now!

1183
01:12:12.165 --> 01:12:13.792
JUNIOR: Look out below!

1184
01:12:16.295 --> 01:12:17.588
Junior. are you okay?

1185
01:12:17.629 --> 01:12:19.423
Yeah. I'm fine. Dad.

1186
01:12:20.424 --> 01:12:22.092
You called me Dad.

1187
01:12:22.759 --> 01:12:24.595
Yeah. I guess I did.

1188
01:12:29.892 --> 01:12:31.602
Get out of the way!

1189
01:12:31.643 --> 01:12:32.811
Hey. he's getting away!

1190
01:12:32.895 --> 01:12:35.522
Nobody messes with the Healys
and gets away. Come on.

1191
01:12:38.066 --> 01:12:39.443
There he is!

1192
01:12:40.611 --> 01:12:43.947
JUNIOR: There's nothing
like going for an outing with your father.

1193
01:12:44.740 --> 01:12:46.116
Wow! Look what I found.

1194
01:12:46.158 --> 01:12:47.534
Hey. that's Roy's.
Give me that.

1195
01:12:47.618 --> 01:12:50.120
Why? You can't drive and
shoot at the same time.

1196
01:12:50.204 --> 01:12:52.122
-What do we do?
-I got an idea.

1197
01:12:55.584 --> 01:12:57.211
Go get him. Dad!

1198
01:12:57.294 --> 01:12:59.046
Faster. son. faster!

1199
01:12:59.546 --> 01:13:00.797
Attaboy!

1200
01:13:01.632 --> 01:13:03.634
Shoot out his tires. Dad!

1201
01:13:04.551 --> 01:13:06.470
-FLO: Hey!
-Don't mess with me!

1202
01:13:09.139 --> 01:13:11.475
FLO: I demand you
stop this car!

1203
01:13:11.975 --> 01:13:14.144
(FLO SCREAMING)

1204
01:13:16.146 --> 01:13:18.148
-What the hell is going on?
-Flo?

1205
01:13:18.190 --> 01:13:19.983
Ben. I want a divorce!

1206
01:13:20.067 --> 01:13:21.652
Shut up. Flo!

1207
01:13:38.001 --> 01:13:39.336
(SCREAMING)

1208
01:13:42.130 --> 01:13:44.508
Stop! Junior. stop!
Hit the brakes!

1209
01:13:45.926 --> 01:13:48.262
(FLO SCREAMING)

1210
01:13:54.935 --> 01:13:56.687
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

1211
01:13:59.481 --> 01:14:02.734
FLO: Now what the hell's going on?
What's that smell?

1212
01:14:03.902 --> 01:14:06.822
Well. Flo always said
she wanted to travel.

1213
01:14:09.825 --> 01:14:11.702
Come on. let's go home.

1214
01:14:12.035 --> 01:14:13.245
OFFICER: Move it!

1215
01:14:16.373 --> 01:14:17.916
You little traitor!

1216
01:14:18.458 --> 01:14:20.252
BEN: No!

1217
01:14:25.507 --> 01:14:28.218
No!

1218
01:14:31.430 --> 01:14:33.015
JUNIOR: Daddy!

1219
01:14:33.056 --> 01:14:37.728
Daddy. please don't go!
I'm sorry for all those bad things I did.

1220
01:14:37.811 --> 01:14:41.773
If you come back. I promise I'll never
do anything naughty again.

1221
01:14:41.857 --> 01:14:45.152
Daddy. come back.
I love you.

1222
01:14:47.321 --> 01:14:49.156
I love you. too. son.

1223
01:14:49.239 --> 01:14:51.575
Dad? I don't believe it.

1224
01:14:52.701 --> 01:14:54.411
I don't believe it. either.

1225
01:14:55.746 --> 01:14:57.372
Are you gonna be okay?

1226
01:14:57.414 --> 01:14:58.582
Yeah.

1227
01:15:00.375 --> 01:15:02.085
But the prune's had it.

1228
01:15:02.127 --> 01:15:03.420
(LAUGHING)

1229
01:15:03.504 --> 01:15:05.422
Lay still. please.
An ambulance is on the way.

1230
01:15:05.464 --> 01:15:08.383
No. I'll be
all right. officer. He got me in the prune.

1231
01:15:09.134 --> 01:15:10.260
Okay.

1232
01:15:10.344 --> 01:15:14.932
Now. you're not gonna hold me to all that
stupid junk I said about being nice. are you?

1233
01:15:15.933 --> 01:15:19.853
Of course not.
I just want you to be yourself.

1234
01:15:20.896 --> 01:15:22.856
Some people never learn.

1235
01:15:24.149 --> 01:15:25.609
Come on. son.

1236
01:15:41.625 --> 01:15:43.043
Come on.

1237
01:15:43.794 --> 01:15:47.840
JUNIOR: Why does this guy love me?
Why do parents love any kid?

1238
01:15:48.257 --> 01:15:51.176
Maybe it's one of those
answers we'll never know. like.

1239
01:15:51.260 --> 01:15:53.971
"How high is up?"
"Why is the sky blue?"

1240
01:15:54.054 --> 01:15:57.224
and "Whatever happened
to Mrs. Healy?"

1241
01:15:57.307 --> 01:15:59.810
Hey. your pig's
making funny noises.

1242
01:15:59.852 --> 01:16:02.646
Yeah. Big Miguel.
he's got a bad stomach.

1243
01:16:03.355 --> 01:16:04.815
(PIGS SQUEALING)

1244
01:16:04.898 --> 01:16:06.650
(PIG FARTING)

1245
01:16:06.900 --> 01:16:08.861
FLO: Oh. my God!
